const char gCompressedText_MSG_07D4[] = ",but remained until the end.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07D5[] = "Eirika, Restoration Queen";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07D6[] = "Eirika returned to Renais and began thereconstruction effort with her brother,Ephraim. Seeing peace return to the livesof her people filled her with happiness.Her smile became a symbol of her people's joy.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07D7[] = "Seth, the Silver Knight";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07D8[] = "Seth returned to Renais with Ephraim and hisfellow knights. His dedicated service made himthe most trusted of the new king and queen'sguardsmen, as well as the most famous ofknights in all of Renais.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07D9[] = "Silent Gilliam";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07DA[] = "Gilliam returned to his home of Frelia, wherehe continued to serve the crown as a faithfulknight. His imposing countenance was said tostrike fear in the hearts of even the mostarrogant and brash of Frelia's new recruits.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07DB[] = "Franz the Faithful";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07DC[] = "He continued to serve Renais with the samedevotion that he had during the War of theStones. His generous nature and easy smilemade him a favorite among the people.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07DD[] = "Moulder, Wise Counselor";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07DE[] = "After the War of the Stones, Mouldercontinued to serve the royal family ofFrelia. His wisdom served to guide King Innes as it had served King Haydenbefore him.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07DF[] = "Vanessa, Dutiful Rider";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E0[] = "She remained on active duty as an airborneknight in Frelia's army. Her beauty anddetermination became the standard to whichher fellow knights aspired.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E1[] = "Ross, His Father's Son";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E2[] = "He returned to Ide, village of his youth,and helped rebuild it after the banditattack that brought it to ruin. Years later,he set out on his own to perfect his fightingskill and hone both body and spirit.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E3[] = "Neimi, the Tearful Archer";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E4[] = "She returned to her village and passedher days in peace and quiet. Years later,she traveled to the capital of Renais asan archery instructor for their military.She never could resist a good cry.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E5[] = "Colm, Good-Natured Thief";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E6[] = "He politely refused an invitation tobecome a spy for Renais, returning insteadto his hometown. He spent the rest of hisdays as a chivalrous rogue helping thosein need from the shadows.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E7[] = "Garcia, the Warrior Reborn";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E8[] = "He returned to Ide to help with itsreconstruction after the bandit attack.Afterward, he reenlisted in the army, servingRenais as a troop leader. His strength,valor, and experience inspired many.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07E9[] = "Innes, King and Strategician";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07EA[] = "As time went on, he succeeded his father,Hayden, as king of Frelia. His resourcefulnessand tactical prowess helped him build a courtof loyal vassals that served to lead thecountry to greater prosperity.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07EB[] = "Lute, Prodigy";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07EC[] = "After the War of the Stones, Lute returned to Renais to continue her arcane studies. She spent far less time locked in her library,preferring now to explore the outside world.She grew into a great and well-traveled sage.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07ED[] = "Natasha, Sacred Healer";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07EE[] = "Once the war was over, Natasha returned toGrado to help rebuild the empire. She dedicatedherself to easing the grief of those familiesthat lost soldiers during the war.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07EF[] = "Cormag, Aloof Lanceman";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F0[] = "Cormag returned to Grado to assist in thereconstruction of his country. Shortlyafter, he left to wander on his own. Whenhe reappeared, he rejoined the army not asa knight but as a common soldier.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F1[] = "Ephraim, Restoration King";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F2[] = "Busy days awaited him upon his return toRenais. He oversaw the rebuilding not onlyof his own country but also of the entirecontinent of Magvel. His work was difficult,but his success made him a legend.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F3[] = "Forde, the Wild Knight";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F4[] = "Upon Forde's return to Renais, his secrethobby of painting was discovered. He wascommissioned as a court artist. His workgrew popular, and his days became so busythat he often regretted his career change.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F5[] = "Kyle, Ardent Knight";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F6[] = "His service to the royal family of Renaiscontinued without change. He became abattalion commander and gained much trustand responsibility for training new recruits.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F7[] = "Amelia, Rose of the War";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F8[] = "Following the war, she returned to Gradoto assist in her country's reconstruction.She surrounded herself with new friends andused the strength she found on the battlefieldto live her life in happiness.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07F9[] = "Artur, Saint of Light";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07FA[] = "Artur moved to Renais to help rebuild theshattered country. He worked without rest toease the pain and grief of those who sufferedduring the war. His self-sacrifice made himinto a folk hero among the peasantry.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07FB[] = "Gerik, the Desert Tiger";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07FC[] = "Gerik continued as a mercenary. Over theyears, his reputation grew so great that hehad more job offers than he could handle. Oneday, without warning, he left, never to return.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07FD[] = "Tethys, Beloved Dancer";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07FE[] = "She danced from city to city, and theentire continent became her stage.Her fame grew and grew, and large crowdsgathered wherever she performed.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_07FF[] = "Marisa, the Crimson Flash";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0800[] = "Marisa became battalion leader for anelite mercenary force. Many men soughtto challenge her to a duel, and noneof them stood up to her blade.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0801[] = "Saleh, the Well of Wisdom";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0802[] = "Saleh returned to Caer Pelyn, where heremained a faithful servant of the Manakete.His days were not spent in isolation, though.Many of the friends he met during the War ofthe Stones came to visit his village.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0803[] = "Ewan, Enthusiastic Student";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0804[] = "Ewan continued his studies, modelinghis life after the teachings of Saleh.Eventually, his education branched off intodifferent paths. His insatiable curiosityled him on a trip to explore the world.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0805[] = "L'Arachel, Queen of Light";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0806[] = "She succeeded her uncle as ruler of theRausten Theocracy several years afterthe war ended. She never lost her...uniqueperspective on life. She spent much of herrule visiting the neighboring countries.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0807[] = "Dozla of the Steady Axe";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0808[] = "As L'Arachel rose to become queen, heremained by her side. Watching L'Arachelgrow to become the queen she was destined tobe was Dozla's greatest joy in life.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0809[] = "Rennac, Rich Merchant";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_080A[] = "L'Arachel summoned Rennac back to Rausten,and he was forced to return. He was neverable to escape his service to the self-centered princess who became queen.Admittedly, he didn't try very hard.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_080B[] = "Duessel, Obsidian General";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_080C[] = "Following the war, Duessel returned to Grado,where he was instrumental in its rebuilding.He spent his remaining years watching overGrado and sharing his wisdom with othernations as an expert combat instructor.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_080D[] = "Myrrh, the Great Dragon";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_080E[] = "After bidding her farewells to Ephraim,she returned to Darkling Woods. She liveda long and full life, served by the peopleof Caer Pelyn and comforted by the memoriesof her dear friends.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_080F[] = "Knoll, Watcher of Darkness";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0810[] = "Knoll returned to Grado, where he dedicatedhimself to rebuilding it and fulfillingLyon's vision. When the country was restoredto its former glory, he disappeared withouta trace, never to be seen again.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0811[] = "Joshua, the Tempest King";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0812[] = "Joshua returned to Jehanna and ruled overit as king. His skills as a leader hadgrown great, and Jehanna flourished asnever before. He never outgrew his loveof travel and games of chance.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0813[] = "Graceful Syrene";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0814[] = "Syrene continued as commander of Frelia'spegasus knights. Her grace and beauty inflight were the subject of many songsand paintings, and her popularity soared.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0815[] = "Tana, Winged Queen";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0816[] = "Tana lived happily in the prosperous post-war Frelia. She flew to Renais often tovisit her dear friend Eirika.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0817[] = "Busy days awaited Eirika and Ephraim as theystruggled to rebuild Renais. Their work gavenew hope to those ravaged by the war, andwith Eirika's constant help, Ephraim grew tobe a trusted and honorable king.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0818[] = "Upon their return to Renais, Eirika and Sethwere wed, with the blessings of Ephraim and allof the Knights of Renais. The tale of the lovethat grew between a princess and her loyalknight became a beloved romance in Renais.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0819[] = "After the war, Eirika and Saleh returned to theirrespective homes. Eirika visited Caer Pelynwhen she could. Eventually, she left Renais inthe care of her brother and wed Saleh. Theirdaughter resembles the legendary Nada Kuya.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_081A[] = "Following the war, Tana and Eirika remainedthe best of friends. They visited one anotherwhen time permitted, and as they grew older,their children shared a bond of friendshipas close as Eirika and Tana themselves did.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_081B[] = "After the war, Eirika and Forde returned toRenais. Eirika spent her days toiling inthe reconstruction of Renais, and he was herfaithful supporter. His portrait of Eirikacaptured the smile he had thought lost forever.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_081C[] = "After the war, Ephraim returned to Renais andMyrrh to Darkling Woods. They both turned theirattention to their respective duties but neverforgot one another. Though Myrrh never againleft Darkling Woods, Ephraim often visited her.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_081D[] = "Ephraim and L'Arachel each returned homeafter the war, but L'Arachel visited Renaisoften. Over time, the two were wed. Theirmarriage threw Rausten into turmoil, butL'Arachel's self-centeredness carried the day.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_081E[] = "Once Renais was stable again, Ephraim andTana were wed. Innes protested vocally, butwhen he saw how happy Tana was, he gave themarriage his blessings. Renais and Freliaare now bound by blood as well as friendship.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_081F[] = "Natasha returned to Renais with Seth, wherethe two were wed. The reconstruction of Renaiskept them busy, but when all the work wasdone, they settled down to live their daysin peace and happiness.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0820[] = "Franz brought Amelia home with him to Renais.Amelia spent a short time in Renais's army,but once she and Franz were married, sheretired her commission. The two had a daughterwho grew to be a great knight herself.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0821[] = "Gilliam and Syrene returned to Frelia, where theywere married. All agreed they were a perfectmatch, and their union was blessed by thecrown and the order of knights. The twocontinued their unwavering service together.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0822[] = "At Innes's request, Vanessa moved intoCastle Frelia where she continued her dutiesas a knight of the realm. Thereafter, theyhad a child and lived happily with theblessing of all around them.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0823[] = "Forde's love for Vanessa grew after the war,and although she loved him as well, sheplaced her duty to Frelia first. Undeterred,Forde moved to Frelia himself. Over time,the two were wed.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0824[] = "Father and son returned to Ide, where theytoiled together to rebuild their village.Ross grew to become a greater warrior thaneven his father. When he himself had a son,that child continued his family's legacy.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0825[] = "The childhood friends became lovers first,then husband and wife. Worried for Neimi'swell-being, Colm gave up his adventurer's ways.Neimi passed on her grandfather's skill inarchery to her own son and daughter.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0826[] = "Artur and Lute were married upon their return.Artur handled the housework, but otherwise,their lives were unchanged. When they had ason, Lute's interests shifted from studyingArtur to studying her son's baffling habits.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0827[] = "After the war, Kyle and Lute were married inRenais. Kyle's friends were disturbed by hischoice of brides, but they could not denyhis happiness. Before long, they had a son,and Kyle dedicated himself to his upbringing.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0828[] = "When Joshua returned to Jehanna, he tookNatasha as his bride and claimed the throneas its rightful heir. Natasha was the perfectcompanion, and together, they carried themighty desert nation to great glory.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0829[] = "Sometimes, the greatest friends also differgreatly in personality. When Kyle and Fordereturned home, they were celebrated in songand story. They lived their days in happiness,as dearest friends and toughest rivals.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_082A[] = "Cormag returned to Grado to assist in thereconstruction of his country. Shortlyafter, he left to wander on his own. Tanaspent years looking for him. In time, shefound him and knighted him in Frelia's service.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_082B[] = "Stories tell of the sparks that flew betweenL'Arachel and Innes when they first met. Asthe love between them flourished, so too didthe bond that united their two nations.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_082C[] = "Gerik and Tethys remained bound to no nationand beholden to no authority. They boughtthemselves a leisurely retirement. Geriktaught fencing to city youths, and Tethysfound many stages on which to dance.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_082D[] = "Gerik remained a mercenary, and Marisabecame his company's fencing instructor.Gerik returned the affection she gavehim, although he was troubled to learn shewas clumsy at everything but fighting.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_082E[] = "Myrrh returned to Darkling Woods, but atSaleh's request, she eventually moved to CaerPelyn. In time, the townsfolk learned totreat her not as the Great Dragon butrather as a normal girl, and she was happy.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_082F[] = "Master and student returned to Caer Pelyn tostudy in peace. Ewan worked hard, and in time,his power grew to rival Saleh's. As equals,the two continued their studies together andexpanded their knowledge ever more.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0830[] = "Joshua returned to Jehanna with Marisa, whereshe pledged service to the crown and becamethe top swordfighter in the land. Joshua stillloved games of chance, but when it came toMarisa, she was ever the winner.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0831[] = "L'Arachel was, in time, made queen of Rausten,with Dozla at her side, as always. Later, Dozlawept like a baby when L'Arachel was wed. Hisemotional outburst is remembered as much as,if not more than, the ceremony itself.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0832[] = "Amelia traveled to Ross's hometown, where shedecided to remain. Over time, the two fell inlove and were wed. Years later they had a sonwho grew into a warrior. As he grew in skilland strength, he surpassed even his father.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0833[] = "After the war, Ewan and Amelia set out, aspromised, on a trip around the world. Theirdeeds along the way made small legends in theregions they visited. In time, Amelia gavebirth to a daughter, and they settled down.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0834[] = "After the war, Joshua challenged Gerik to aduel in hopes of pressing him to move toJehanna. The match ended in a tie, but Gerikwas impressed by Joshua's swagger. From thatday forward, Gerik never left Joshua's side.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0835[] = "Sisters Syrene and Vanessa returned to Freliaafter the war for a long-overdue talk. Theytalked of love and war, of friends now gone.Together, they renewed their bond as siblingsand vowed never to let that bond fail.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0836[] = "After the reconstruction of Renais, Inneschallenged Ephraim to a duel. The matchended in a tie. After the fight, Eirikaacknowledged her love for Innes, and thetwo were wed with Ephraim's blessings.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0837[] = "After the war, Kyle visited Frelia, wherehe was greeted with a warm reception bySyrene. After the two retired, they werewed. They raised a daughter whose skillin martial arts and etiquette excelled.";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0838[] = "Upon their return to Grado, Duessel reunitedAmelia with her mother. The two wept withjoy, giving thanks to Duessel. Afterward, Ameliabecame the most trusted companion of theman once known as Obsidian.";
