const char gCompressedText_MSG_08DB[] = "The continent of Magvel.\x03For some 800 years, a quiet peace reigned in the absence of the terrible darkness.\x03The Sacred Stones have been passed from generation to generation.\x03Nations have been built around their power and their legacy.\x03The kingdom of Renais, ruled by Fado, the peerless Warrior King.\x03The kingdom of Frelia, ruled by Hayden, the venerable Sage King.\x03The kingdom of Jehanna, ruled by Ismaire, Queen of the White Dunes.\x03The theocracy of Rausten, ruled by Mansel, the Divine Emperor.\x03The Grado Empire, ruled by Vigarde, the stalwart Silent Emperor.\x03These five countries house the power of the Sacred Stones.\x03They are joined by the emerging mercantile republic of Carcino.\x03In these times of peace, tales of pastconflict have drifted into legend,\x03and memories of the ancient dark artshave all but evaporated.\x03It is now the year 803...\x03In an instant, the whole of Magvel is threatened by an unexpected atrocity.\x03The Grado Empire, the largest of the Sacred Stone nations,\x03has invaded the kingdom of Renais under orders from Emperor Vigarde.\x03A longtime ally of Grado, Renais is caughtoff guard, unable to mount any resistance.\x03Grado's forces move quickly, seizing oneterritory after another.\x03Compounding King Fado's worries, his son,Prince Ephraim, has gone missing.\x03Grado's momentum carries its armies to the gates of Castle Renais itself.\x03Renais will fall...It is inevitable.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08DC[] = "Eirika and her companions have liberated the border castle.\x03Alongside Princess Tana of Frelia, they ride to the Frelian capital.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08DD[] = "The world map shows the continent in its entirety.\x03Castles, towns, and other map pointsare added to the map as you play.\x03Press the A Button when not on a map point to open the !map menu!.\x03This is where you can !save!.When you want to stop playing, use this option to save your progress.\x03Now then, move on to your nextdestination.\x03The marker with the !red flag! in the centerof the map is your destination.\x03Move the triangle cursor onto the red flag and press the A Button.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08DE[] = "King Hayden apologizes for being unable to spare soldiers.\x03However, he does provide Eirika with a small but trusted party of vassals.\x03Eirika is grateful for the king's aid.\x03Chasing rumors of her brother, she sets out for Grado.\x03The group's first stop is the remote village of Ide, which was, until very recently, \x03a part of Renais.\x03Here, Eirika sees the devastation of Renais with her own eyes.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08DF[] = "Once cleared, battle sites become !bases!. You can !manage items! on any base.\x03To manage items, place the cursor on your character icon.\x03Then, press the A Button to bring up the!Manage Items! command.\x03Choose Manage Items to trade possessionswith your supply convoy or with other units.\x03Some map areas have !shops!and !armories!.\x03To see if a base has a shop or anarmory, move the cursor to that base.\x03For example, in Ide, where Eirika isnow, there is an !armory!.\x03Check the corner of the screen for the!base name! and any !shop icons!.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E0[] = "Eirika and company pursue the thief who stole her bracelet.\x03Their chase leads them into the mountains,where Bazba's Bandits pillage at will.\x03Eirika cannot ignore her countrymen's pleas for help.\x03She leads her group in search of the bandits' stronghold.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E1[] = "With her bracelet recovered, Eirika setsout with renewed determination.\x03Passing through the ancient forest Za'ha brings them close to Grado's border.\x03As they near the town of Serafew, Eirika'sfears are assuaged by the lack of troops.\x03But never-before-seen terrors crawl in the shadows of the trees.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E2[] = "An ominous wave of dark creatures washes over the continent...\x03Eirika's journey to find her brother, Ephraim, grows ever more perilous.\x03Still, she presses on despite the danger. Her will is strong.\x03The town of Serafew, located on the border of Renais and Grado.\x03The people of both countries have long used the town as a meeting place.\x03It stands as testimony to the friendship the two nations have shared these many years.\x03Now, however, Serafew is teeming with Grado troops.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E3[] = "Eirika suppresses her feelings of unease and continues to search for her brother.\x03Passing through Serafew, the group crosses into the Grado Empire.\x03From here forward, there is no doubt thatthey are walking through hostile territory.\x03In hopes of avoiding unnecessary trouble,\x03Eirika and company head for a sparselypopulated region of Grado.\x03However, it is too late. Their movements are already being tracked.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E4[] = "Rumors say that Ephraim has been defeated and taken prisoner.\x03Now Eirika must find a way to rescue her brother from beneath enemy eyes.\x03Eirika's company rushes toward Castle Renvall, where Ephraim is being held.\x03Surrounded by lakes, Renvall is a naturalfortress, all but unassailable.\x03A lone bridge, held by the enemy, is itsonly entrance.\x03Eirika has only one choice.\x03Eirika decides to confront Grado's soldiers head on...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E5[] = "The !Tower of Valni! has appeared to theeast of Castle Frelia on the world map.\x03Once held by Grado's troops, it has becomehome to a host of !dark creatures!.\x03Battling these monstrosities is a good way for units to gain strength.\x03Try using the tower as a training area to gain extra experience.\x03Be aware: you cannot save your battle preparations for tower skirmishes.\x03Once you clear a tower map, you'll have access to the next floor.\x03Each floor is more difficult than the last, so come prepared!\x03Dark creatures also may appear on other bases on the world map.\x03To engage these demons in combat,\x03simply place the cursor on their location and press the A Button.\x03If the battle goes poorly and you're in danger of losing units,\x03use the !retreat! command on the map menu to withdraw your troops.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E6[] = "Eirika chooses to travel by sea to the theocracy of Rausten.\x03Her search for a ship leads her to Port Kiris in Carcino.\x03Carcino is a young nation ruled by a councilof merchants, and it is an ally of Frelia.\x03Carcino council leader Klimt, a staunch opponent of Grado's imperialistic actions,\x03has pledged Carcino's support to Frelia in this conflict.\x03Prince Innes also intends to pass through Carcino on his way to Jehanna.\x03Eirika believes there is nothing to fear in Carcino, but she is wrong.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E7[] = "Carcino has betrayed Frelia and joined forces with Grado.\x03Carcino's troops stop Prince Innes, blockinghis way to Jehanna.\x03With soldiers occupying the road forward and back, he is trapped in a hopeless situation.\x03Eirika rushes to the prince's aid.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E8[] = "The Caer Pelyn Range...\x03According to Ewan, a little-known passage to Jehanna lies there,\x03hidden within its cracked red bedrock and knife-edged peaks.\x03To avoid Carcino and combat, Eirika'stroops take the mountain path.\x03They begin climbing higher and higher toward Caer Pelyn.\x03Unbeknownst to the group, hordes of dark creatures now roam the peaks.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08E9[] = "Jehanna, home of dancing white sands.\x03This largely barren desert nation is infamous for its mercenary forces.\x03In accordance with her husband's dying wish, the beautiful Ismaire rules Jehanna.\x03The Queen of the White Dunes governs Jehanna with grace and honor.\x03When he was young, her son left Jehanna.His whereabouts remain unknown.\x03After passing through Caer Pelyn, Eirika arrives in Jehanna.\x03There, she finds the nation embroiled in combat with Grado's forces.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08EA[] = "Thanks to the arrival of reinforcementsfrom Princess L'Arachel of Rausten,\x03Eirika and her allies successfully repel the Grado invaders.\x03Still, Jehanna Hall remains under siege, on the edge of ruin.\x03En route, Eirika learns that the hall has indeed been captured by Grado.\x03To rescue Queen Ismaire and recover Jehanna's Sacred Stone,\x03Eirika leads an assault on the royal hall.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08EB[] = "Jehanna Hall has capitulated to Grado's forces and the Knights of Rausten,\x03who rode to Jehanna's aid, have been routed by General Valter.\x03On their own again, Eirika and company flee into the desert.\x03Without mercy, Generals Valter and Caellach come hunting.\x03Eirika is soon brought to ground.Enemy forces close in on all sides.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08EC[] = "The capital of Renais.\x03After the twins' absence, seeing their homeruined by war brings them terrible grief.\x03Orson, a former Knight of Renais, had been assigned to guard Castle Renais.\x03However, he switched allegiances, betraying his oaths of loyalty to his homeland.\x03Eirika marks her homecoming by vowing to see Renais healed.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08ED[] = "The Sacred Stones that defeated the DemonKing radiate a constant and dazzling light.\x03The Sacred Stones are the only power againstthe dark, the last hope of humanity. \x03It is only natural that evil would seekto destroy the Sacred Stones...\x03There can be no other force behind thisattempt to gain the stones.\x03A childhood friend appears before Eirika.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08EE[] = "The group sets off in search of Grado's elusive Imperial Prince Lyon.\x03Innes has ordered Frelian troops to aid in the hunt.\x03The troops return with news that Lyon has moved north.\x03The group's search for Lyon leads them to Mt. Neleras, in the heart of Darkling Woods.\x03The scorching heat and sulphur stench render the area unfit for human habitation...\x03Endless numbers of gorgon eggs stud the forbidding landscape. \x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08EF[] = "The Sacred Stone of Renais has been broken.\x03Constant strife with dark creatures hasmade the group's progress near impossible.\x03Princess L'Arachel of Rausten suggests theypay a visit to Rausten Court.\x03It is here that the final Sacred Stoneis sealed away.\x03L'Arachel rides cheerfully toward her homeland with the company in tow.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F0[] = "According to legend, the Sacred Stones have sealed evil away from the world.\x03Four of the five stones have been destroyed,leaving only the last stone intact.\x03The last stone must be protected to staveoff the Demon King's restoration.\x03Eirika and company challenge the demons of Darkling Woods.\x03According to legend,\x03the original possessors of the Sacred Stonesdefeated the Demon King in Darkling Woods.\x03His foul blood seeped into the land,corrupting every seed and every root.\x03The once-pristine forest was transformed bythe flood of disease and venom.\x03Legend says the Demon King's corpse lies there still, not dead but dreaming.\x03Dreaming of when the last stone is crushed,\x03and he will rise from his bed of rocks and worms and return to the surface.\x03Within Darkling Woods, hideous fiends roamin increasing numbers, as if responding\x03to some unheard call...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F1[] = "Ephraim begins his march south towardGrado from Castle Frelia.\x03Upon conquering Renais, the Grado Empirehas set its sights on Frelia.\x03However, Innes and his troop meet the invaders at the waters' edge.\x03Against all odds, Innes halts the invasion, keeping Frelia's border intact.\x03Ephraim coordinates Frelia's troops in aneffort to advance the front lines.\x03Unbeknownst to Ephraim, Grado forces are waiting for them at Fort Rigwald.\x03They've fortified their positions and planto wait out Frelia's siege.\x03Undaunted, Ephraim remains determined to root out Grado.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F2[] = "A former lance instructor to Ephraim,\x03Grado's General Duessel often came to Renais as an emissary of his empire.\x03Despite their stations, the two men share similar dispositions and a warm relationship.\x03Why has Grado started this war?\x03What is the miasma of evil emanating from the country?\x03Ephraim believes that Duessel can answerthese questions.\x03It is this belief that propels Ephraimforward into Grado territory.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F3[] = "General Duessel tells them of the enigmatic Dark Stone.\x03The product of Grado's research into the dark arts, \x03the Dark Stone possesses power far beyond that of the Sacred Stones.\x03According to the rumors swirling about, \x03Vigarde's descent into madness coincides with the creation of the Dark Stone.\x03Ephraim must confirm the existence ofthe Dark Stone. \x03He decides to travel to Grado by sea.\x03Midway through their passage, however,an eerie fog begins to form...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F4[] = "Ephraim leads the group to Za'albul Marsh in search of the missing Myrrh.\x03They learn from soldiers and villagers that Myrrh had been captured by General Selena, \x03one of Grado's commanders.She was last seen heading east.\x03To regain their companion, the group will now be forced to fight.\x03Ephraim steels his heart to the realitythat he must face Selena.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F5[] = "Myrrh returns safely to Ephraim's side.\x03A noble warrior to the end, Selena foughtwith great honor, \x03never once using Myrrh as a hostage.\x03Ephraim renews his vow to pierce the veil of mystery surrounding the Grado Empire.\x03Selena is added to the list of innocents who Grado must account for.\x03The center of the Grado Empire. EmperorVigarde should have been here, but...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_08F6[] = "Ephraim's sister is in danger.\x03Grado's General Caellach has attacked Jehanna Hall, forcing its surrender.\x03Though Eirika and her troop have left the Hall, Grado's forces pursue them relentlessly.\x03Trapped in the burning desert, enemy forcesclose in on them from all sides. \x03With no time to wait for Frelia's troops, Ephraim leaves for Jehanna immediately.\x03He must go to his sister's aid.\x03";
