const char gCompressedText_MSG_093B[] = "	[	The rumors are true, aren't they? TheGrado army's taken over the castle.\x03It looks like they've seized thecastle gate, too.\x03Smart work--the gate provides defenseand heals wounds to boot.\x03They must be fierce warriors to havetaken the gate. Watch yourself.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_093C[] = "	\\	That knight encamped at the castle waswearing the finest armor I've seen.\x03It looked like it could turn aside almostany blade you swing at it.\x03I know my armor, though. I wager a goodrapier or armorslayer could get through it.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_093D[] = "The relationship between !swords!, !lances!,and !axes! is called the !weapon triangle!.\x03!Lances! are strong against !swords!.!Swords! are strong against !axes!.!Axes! are strong against !lances!.\x03In that last battle, the enemy commander,Breguet, wielded a !lance!, while theFrelian soldier used a !sword!.\x03!Lances! are strong against !swords!,so Breguet had an advantage.\x03The !weapon triangle! can be veryimportant in determining the outcome ofa battle. For the time being, just\x03remember that !lances! are strongagainst !swords!.\x03";
