const char gCompressedText_MSG_09D7[] = "	8B	What a pleasant surprise.It's Master Valter.\x03What's the situation, Tirado? Youhave captured Ephraim, haven't you?\x03	No. Prince Ephraim still fightsin the lands north of Renvall.\x03And why is that?\x03What has happened to allthose mercenaries you hired?\x03	They've proven to be less than adequate.\x03Ephraim's clever. His band strikes quicklyand then vanishes into the woods.\x03We more than double his numbers, and yethe uses the terrain wisely to fight us.\x03He has no army--just a small forceof knights loyal to Renais.\x03Prince Ephraim's reputation as a superbstrategist would seem to be well earned.\x03Hmm...\x03How interesting. The lad's beginningto whet my appetite.\x03Tirado... Bring him to me as quicklyas you can, will you?\x03	As you command.\x03Just grant me an army, andI'll bring him down swiftly.\x03What sort of plan do you have?\x03	Master, I am your loyal adjutant,and you are my general.\x03For you, my lord, I have manyplans ready and waiting.\x03Really? Well then,let me hear them.\x03	Very well. \x03First, you and I will leave thisfort and head north.\x03Then, we will find Prince Ephraimin his leafy playpen.\x03But he's not easily found, is he?\x03	Do not worry.\x03At Prince Ephraim's side is...a friend, shall we say.\x03When the time is right, our friendwill move on our behalf...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_09D8[] = "	\x13	Forde, how are we onsupplies and equipment?\x03It's not looking good.\x03Our weapons are in bad shape,and we're running low on food.\x03We can probably restock at anearby village, but--\x03	No, that's not an option.\x03We're in enemy territory. I will notinvolve innocents if I can avoid it.\x03Yeah, I knew you'd say that.\x03I mean, it's because of stuff like thatthat we've stuck with you so far.\x03But eventually, we do need to facereality. What are we going to do?\x03\x13Word of mouth has it that the invasionof Renais has progressed quite far.\x03I've heard that the capital has fallen.\x03	Hm... So soon...\x03Still, my father is in the capital,and he won't surrender easily.\x03Forde, Kyle.\x03Our mission here is to harry thetroops, to distract their eye.\x03Hopefully, we'll be able to give myfather and Eirika time to escape.\x03	Kyle, have you heard anything fromOrson? I sent him ahead to scout.\x03\x13No word yet, and it's abouttime he returned...\x03\x13EReporting in, Prince Ephraim.\x03I can confirm Grado presence atseveral points around our camp.\x03Also, a large battalion of soldiershas been dispatched from Renvall.\x03We shouldn't tarry here any longerthan necessary...\x03	I see.\x03Seems as though we've certainlycaught Grado's eye this time.\x03Should we retreat back to thecapital, Prince Ephraim?\x03	No. We press onward.\x03We're going to capture Renvall.\x03Wh-what?!?\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_09D9[] = "	\x13	So this is Renvall, is it?\x03All right, let's go.\x03Um... Are you...sure you'requite sane, Prince Ephraim?\x03We've an entire army after us, andyou want to charge their stronghold?\x03\x13" "Forde! Watch your tongue! This is our prince you're addressing!\x03	Kyle, please, it's all right.We've heard nothing from home,\x03so what harm could a littlereckless besieging cause?\x03\x13Prince Ephraim...\x03	Don't worry. I haven't lost all senseof self-preservation.\x03Renvall holds an important place inGrado's national defense.\x03If we can get the upper handand take control of it,\x03then Grado will waste many valuablesoldiers trying to take it back.\x03I hope our attack proves usefulto my father and Eirika.\x03I understand what you're saying, but...\x03can we do it with our current strength?\x03	Every soldier in this area istrying to find us.\x03The enemy has us vastly outnumbered.Attacking the castle is a ridiculous idea.\x03If the enemy thinks the same...then we may have our opening.\x03You have a point. I'm sure Renvall won'texpect us to attack with these numbers.\x03Either way, we can't run forever.And we're running out of supplies.\x03What've we got to lose?Shall we get ready to go?\x03	Yes. If we don't move quickly, wemay never get another chance.\x03Trust me. I don't pick fights Icannot win.\x03\x13Yes, sir!\x03";
