const char gCompressedText_MSG_09E3[] = "	B	So, you've captured Renvall, have you?And with such a small force! Impressive!\x03You've earned your reputation. I must say,I quite admire your work.\x03I take it you're the leader of thispack--the misguided Prince Ephraim.\x03I am.\x03	I'm General Valter, the Moonstoneof Grado's Imperial Army.\x03Catching up to you has caused meno small amount of trouble.\x03We've reduced your wretched homeof Renais to ruin, and yet...\x03you and your little band of bravoscontinue to be a thorn in our side.\x03But that all ends here.\x03\x13We'll see... You claim you'vetaken the capital of Renais...\x03Tell me, how did you knowI would attack Renvall?\x03	Ha ha... Patience. You'll haveyour answer soon enough.\x03Now, be good lads, and dropyour weapons, will you?\x03\x13\x13Prince Ephraim, let us attack!\x03......\x03	Listen to me, Ephraim. You're a smartman. You know it's futile to fight me.\x03You cannot win.You cannot escape.\x03Accept the reality of your situation,and surrender to me.\x03Surrender?\x03	Heh heh heh... That's right.If you do, I'll let you live.\x03I hold your life in the palm of myhand. Do not test my good humor.\x03Now come over here, bend yourknee, and beg for your life.\x03Show me how Renais dogs grovel.\x03I think not.\x03	What?\x03You said your name was Valter, didn't you?\x03Well, I'm sorry, Valter, but I don't havetime to waste playing games with you.\x03So, we're going to knock you louts about abit and then make our way out of here.\x03	Fool... Have you gone mad?\x03Do you truly believe you can fightyour way past my wyvern knights?\x03Watch and see. I don't pickfights I can't win.\x03Kyle, Forde.Are you ready?\x03\x13My life has been yours since themoment I took my chivalric vows.\x03\x13\x13\x13It's moments like these thatkeep me by your side, my prince.\x03\x13	What idiotic wretches you are...\x03Prepare yourselves to bedestroyed utterly!\x03We break to the east. GO!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_09E4[] = "	H6	So, tell me...\x03You have ascertained Eirika'swhereabouts, have you not?\x03I have.\x03I sent some of our men to followthe princess as she fled Serafew.\x03They tell me Eirika and her friendswill be coming this way shortly.\x03Our ambush is ready and waiting.There's no way they can escape.\x03Like rats in a sack, as they say.Heh heh heh...\x03	Very good...Won't that wretched Valter be delighted.\x03Now about this Princess Eirika...I hear she's quite a handful.\x03They say her paladin withstoodValter's lance...\x03Tell me, Novala, are you certain youcan handle this assignment?\x03Don't worry. Everythingis under control.\x03I've brought along a certainsomething from Renais.\x03It will negate whatever futileresistance they offer. Ha ha ha...\x03	Heh heh heh...Pray it goes as you say.\x03Very well. Do what you must.I must return to the capital.\x03Will you not stay and see howEirika looks in captivity?\x03	Unlike two other layabouts I know,I do not have such time to waste.\x03I have much to do for our master.A mountain of tasks awaits me.\x03My time is far too precious to wasteon the likes of that royal whelp.\x03Trifles such as these are best left inthe hands of servants...such as you.\x03Y-yes, of course...\x03Then...travel well.\x03	Hmph...Freakish old man.\x03You should have watched. You mighthave learned something.\x03I will capture the princess, and I willreplace you at our master's side.\x03You will stew in regret, and I willenjoy every moment.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_09E5[] = "\n\x136\x13Ha ha ha...\x03Princess Eirika of Renais!\x03Accept your fate. You havenowhere to flee!\x03\nWhat?!Who are you?\x03And where...where didyou come from?\x03\x13You're as beautiful as I'd heard...And you're even wearing your bracelet.\x03I suppose we should begin there. Wouldyou surrender your lovely little trinket?\x03Ah!\x03\nMy bracelet...\x03Why do you want it?\x03\x13His Majesty desires it.That's reason enough.\x03Once I present it to him, he will makeme a general, and I will be famous.\x03Come, hand it over. Do it quickly,and I'll leave you alive.\x03Princess Eirika, you will do no such thing.\x03\nOf course not.\x03\x13Obedience will save you pain.\x03You came all this way to aidPrince Ephraim, have you not?\x03A fool's errand. Ephraim fell beforethe empire's might.\x03As we speak he wastes away in a cell inRenvall, meekly awaiting his execution.\x03\nMy brother?!\x03You lie! A pitiful worm like youcould never defeat my brother!\x03\x13" "Bah. Protest all you like.It does not change the truth.\x03Ephraim has lost, and it wasGrado that defeated him!\x03\n......\x03\x13You're not going to acquiesce,are you? Very well.\x03Bring me the child.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_09E6[] = "\nc\x136H-help me...\x03\nAh!\x03\x13Look familiar? She's a citizenof your precious Renais.\x03Now give me the bracelet!Do it, or the child dies!\x03\nNo, please...\x03You win. But I must have your wordthe child will suffer no harm.\x03Princess, wait.That bracelet--\x03\nIt's not worth a child's life.\x03Forgive me, Seth.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_09E7[] = "\nc\x136\x13Yes...there can be no mistaking it!\x03Next, your weapons. Take them offand hand them over.\x03No.\x03Surrendering our weapons would betantamount to suicide.\x03You demand too much of us.\x03\x13I see years of peace and idleness have notdulled the wits of all Renais's knights.\x03Well then, my hostage has no more use tome, does she? Ah, such a waste.\x03Wait a moment...I've just had a delicious idea.\x03Have you heard of the giant spiders prowlingabout this region?\x03They'd appreciate a nice, hot meal, wouldn'tyou agree?\x03\nYou can't--\x03Nooo!\x03\x13Ha ha! This will be a delight to watch!\x03These fools will curse the day theywere born to Renais!\x03\nWhy...why would you...\x03How can you do such a thing?\x03\x13This is WAR! There are no rules here!In war, you can do anything! Anything!\x03You curs of Renais have lost! Youridiotic ravings mean nothing...\x03\nEnough. Hold your tongue.\x03\x13Wha...what?!\x03\nI...\x03We, the people of Renais, have long honoredour allegiance with the Grado Empire.\x03And you invaded without warning. Youravaged our land. You killed my father...\x03Even then, I told myself I must not hateGrado or her people.\x03If I gave in to my hate, the bond betweenour lands would be lost forever.\x03I refused to hate. Instead, I lived for theday our nations would know peace again.\x03But...\x03If this is Grado's true face...\x03If you could extinguish Renais without pity, without remorse...\x03If this is the case, then there is no roomin my heart for forgiveness.\x03\x13Impudent girl!\x03Do you expect your words to saveyour countrymen? They will not.\x03Your beloved people will all die,as will you.\x03";
