const char gCompressedText_MSG_09F2[] = "		Your late father, King Fado...\x03He ordered me to keep silent untilthe proper time arrived.\x03However, with all that has happened,with Emperor Vigarde's actions...\x03I feel it imperative that I tellyou everything, Princess Eirika.\x03Are you ready to hear the secretof the bracelet you wear?\x03I am...\x03	As you know, Princess...\x03Renais houses one of thelegendary Sacred Stones.\x03Of course. It's in the temple. It'ssupposed to be a ward against evil.\x03	Yes, the true stone is. But the stonein the temple is nothing but a forgery.\x03The real Sacred Stone of Renais liesbeneath the royal castle.\x03Guarding it is a powerful seal, aninfinitely complex lock of sorts.\x03What?\x03Is this true?\x03	Yes. King Fado confided in me himself.\x03The Sacred Stones banished evil long agoand possess powers beyond our ken.\x03The ancient kings of Renais felt itprudent to seal ours away.\x03They feared its power could be misused.They thought to remove the temptation.\x03The keys to break the seal were hidden,too... Forged into bracelets...\x03...The very ones that you and yourbrother, Prince Ephraim, wear.\x03Our bracelets?\x03How could Father keep this asecret from me for so long?\x03	They must know nothing of the bracelets.Tell them only if some great peril strikes.\x03These were King Fado's exact orders.\x03Prince Ephraim knows nothing of thebracelets' secret, either.\x03The king told me this out of fear thatsomething might happen to him.\x03So that, when the time came, the two of youwould learn the truth.\x03The bracelets have such meaning...\x03	Yes. And we are the only living souls whoknow the secret of the Stone of Renais.\x03At least, that's what I was given tobelieve. And yet...\x03Yet the Grado army has made it clearthat they want me only for my bracelet.\x03	Yes, quite clear at that...\x03I don't know how, but Emperor Vigardemust have learned the secret somehow.\x03And now, his troops pursue the bracelet, andwe are no closer to knowing his motives.\x03He would use the bracelets to unlock theSacred Stone and destroy it in secret...\x03	Perhaps.\x03Which means that my brother...and his bracelet...\x03	If he's been captured, they may have thebracelet already, and he may be--\x03Ephraim...\x03	Princess, we must take Novala's words tobe true. We must hurry to Prince Ephraim.\x03The enemy soldiers who fled the battle willhave reported our location by now.\x03If the prince is being held prisonerat Renvall...\x03I fear they might execute him once theylearn of our approach.\x03You're right. We've no time to waste.\x03We must hurry to Renvall!Let's go rescue my brother!\x03";
