const char gCompressedText_MSG_0B29[] = "\n\x13\"\nI see unfamiliar faces among you here,so allow me to introduce myself.\x03I am Ephraim, Eirika's brother andcrown prince of Renais.\x03\x13I'm Princess L'Arachel of Rausten.The pleasure is mine, of course.\x03\nI'll begin by telling you ofhow we've fared in our mission.\x03We seized the Grado capital anddefeated her emperor, Vigarde.\x03Grado's capital guard have, to a man,surrendered and laid down their arms.\x03Pockets of resistance remain, but thewar itself is over.\x03Is that so?\x03\nHowever, something remains thatstill bothers me.\x03A Grado man named Knoll told me aboutsomething called a Dark Stone.\x03\nTheir mages had uncovered lore that ledthem to craft a powerful magic stone.\x03This Dark Stone may have been thecatalyst of Grado's transformation.\x03It seems to be the source of that blackwave of energy Myrrh described.\x03\nVigarde died some time ago, but the powerof the stone played him like a puppet.\x03The war and everything that passed sincewas planned by the Dark Stone's master.\x03Well? Who is it?\x03\n...I still can't believe it,but I'll tell you nonetheless.\x03According to Knoll, the man behindthis is Lyon, the imperial prince.\x03He said Lyon's got the Dark Stone.\x03Figures it's Prince Lyon...\x03No, that doesn't make any sense.\x03Ephraim and I know Lyon better thanthat. We've been friends for years.\x03Lyon's not the sort of person whocould start a war like this.\x03But, Eirika...\x03I saw Lyon recently.\x03Ephraim, you might know this, but afterI abandoned the sea route to Rausten,\x03I traveled overland with PrinceInnes to Jehanna.\x03We ran into trouble with Grado'sforces, and I chanced upon Lyon.\x03He didn't share the details of hissituation, but he intimated that\x03he was on our side. Despite allappearances, he was on our side.\x03So Lyon...\x03\nEirika,I also met Lyon.\x03Did you really?\x03\nYes. But, he was like acompletely different person.\x03To be honest, he didn't seemto be completely...human.\x03Ephraim...What are you saying?\x03\nI'll tell you what I saw.\x03I found Lyon inside Grado Keep.\x03This is what he told me:He said he was behind this war.\x03He said he'd befriended us solely so that,one day, he could invade Renais...\x03He told me he killed our father.\x03That... That can't...\x03\nI know. I can't believe it either.I refuse to believe it.\x03How could he have planned allthis since he was a child...\x03I simply can't fathom it.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0B2A[] = "\nI've heard Lyon changed when he acquiredthe Dark Stone.\x03I've no interest in magic, but...There was something uncanny about him.\x03It seemed almost as though he were beingcontrolled by something himself.\x03......\x03The two of you might find this hardto accept, but...\x03The state of Prince Lyon's heart matterslittle. He has the Dark Stone.\x03That rock is the cause of all that'shappened. The prince must be stopped.\x03\x13Not yet. There is somethingthat needs doing first.\x03L'Arachel?\x03\x13Prince Ephraim, I do believe youfelt it as well.\x03The Dark Stone held by Prince Lyon...It exudes a malefic miasma...\x03We might be able to handle Prince Lyonalone, but that stone is beyond our ken.\x03Then what do you suggest?\x03\x13The Sacred Stones.\x03The Sacred Stones?\x03\x13We've all heard the legend of thefive Sacred Stones.\x03They alone possessed the power toseal the Demon King away forever.\x03So, of course, to dispel demonicmagic, we must use the Sacred Stones!\x03You expect us to pin the outcomeof this war on some fool legend?\x03\n...Not just the legend.We also have hope.\x03\nAccording to Lyon,\x03he has already seen to the destruction ofGrado's, Frelia's, and Jehanna's stones.\x03Hm. That explains something...\x03Grado forces attacked me, intent ondestroying the Stone of Renais.\x03If that could be the reason theychose to invade Renais...\x03The power of the Sacred Stones maybe greater than we'd ever known.\x03\x13Yes, exactly!\x03If we acquire a Sacred Stone, we'll beable to oppose the Dark Stone's might!\x03But three of the stones have beenshattered, and our options are few.\x03Do you suppose that, during theinvasion of Renais...\x03\nNo, I don't think so.\x03The Stone of Renais is hidden by thepower of Eirika's and my bracelets.\x03Grado has made many attemptsto take our bracelets.\x03Every one has failed, and sothe stone may still be safe.\x03\nWe have to confirm that, of course.\x03We've defeated Grado, and we mustturn our eyes to our homeland.\x03It's time to return to Renais.\x03";
