const char gCompressedText_MSG_0B61[] = "P\n-.How do you intend to use theSacred Stone, Lyon?\x03Do you really think you cantap into its power?\x03Mm... My research isn't complete yet,but there's no mistaking the power\x03the Sacred Stones contain.\x03And the Stone of Grado seems especiallyresponsive to my dark magic.\x03I suppose it's because it containsboth sacred and demonic properties.\x03Regardless, if I can just pressmy studies a little harder...\x03Well, I think I might be able to useit to heal my father's illness.\x03If that works, there's no telling howmany other people I can help as well.\x03\nDo you think this is wise?\x03The power contained within the stonesis beyond our understanding...\x03My father tells me that the stonespossess a power not to be trifled with.\x03Uh-huh...Father MacGregor is also against it.\x03That's why they still won't give medirect access to the Stone of Grado.\x03For the time being, I've made do withthe radiant energies surrounding it.\x03They're nothing compared to the rawpower of the stone itself, but...\x03If I can show Father MacGregor somereal progress, perhaps one day...\x03Using the Sacred Stones tostudy magic...\x03Ephraim, Eirika, what do youtwo think?\x03Using the divine power of theSacred Stones in this way...\x03You don't think it's a verygood idea, do you?\x03...It's just that I know nothingat all of magic.\x03I would that there were some way Icould help you, but I simply can't.\x03But, Lyon, I've seen how hard you'veworked to help others.\x03I know how much you want the powerto make others happy.\x03I know these things, and because Iknow you, I trust your intentions.\x03Ephraim...\x03If you hope to use the power of theSacred Stone for good, I trust you can.\x03I'm behind you all the way.\x03\nI agree with Ephraim entirely.\x03You spend every night in the library,studying cures for your father's illness.\x03The power of the Sacred Stones is toopowerful to be used for personal gain.\x03But you, Lyon... I think you'll befine. You're the kindest person I know.\x03Thanks, both of you.\x03Hearing those words from you means alot to me.\x03Actually--and this hasn't been madepublic yet--but...\x03I've already saved someone using theknowledge I've gleaned so far.\x03You have?\x03Uh-huh...\x03A while back, a fire ravaged Serafew, anda little girl got trapped in the flames.\x03Her burns were terrible: not even healingstaves were able to cure her injuries.\x03But just a sliver of the stone's powerrestored her life and healed her wounds.\x03We saved that girl's life, Ephraim!\x03Oh, if you could have seen the tearsof joy in her mother's eyes!\x03You really did it, huh?You are special, Lyon.\x03Congratulations!\x03Well...thanks. But there's still somuch more to be done.\x03I am happy, though. To be honest, Ijust want to be able to help people.\x03I want to put the ancient magics touse for the common good...\x03That's how I feel.\x03\nLyon...\x03And as my research moves forward,I'll be able to do much more, too.\x03We have only the barest understandingof how dark magic operates.\x03Maybe we can use it not only to healwounds, but also to stop diseases...\x03What if we can read the future,predict disasters, move mountains!?\x03\nHold on, Lyon. You can't take toomuch on yourself all at once.\x03What good is helping people ifyou sacrifice yourself to do it?\x03Oh... Yes, of course. Sorry.I got carried away.\x03You have a soft heart, Lyon.\x03I bet you haven't taken anyreal time off at all.\x03So this is what we're going to do.Today, we're going into the city.\x03And you're going with us, Lyon.\x03What?\x03But, Ephraim, you've got ahistory report due.\x03We're taking today off.C'mon, let's go.\x03PBu-but, Ephraim...\x03\nIt's just one day, and I won't tellanyone.\x03Won't it be fun for the three of usto spend a day in the city?\x03Ephraim, Eirika...\x03Thanks so much.\x03I'm lucky to have thetwo of you as friends.\x03";
