const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C5B[] = "\"Eirika... Please holdfor a moment.\x03		What is it, L'Arachel?\x03About what we were discussing earlier...\x03I would not want you to get the wrongidea.\x03I was not saying I was lonely becausemy parents were dead.\x03I am not that weak, you know?\x03I have never even...cried...whenthinking of my parents.\x03	I know, L'Arachel.You are a very strong person.\x03We are lucky to have you with us.\x03I hope you do not think thisall too sudden, but...\x03Here. Look at this.\x03	What's this...?\x03This ruby has been in Rausten forgenerations. It is a valuable gem.\x03I would be honored if... I wouldlike for you to have it.\x03	What? No, I couldn't! It'sfar too precious to accept...\x03No, I mean it. Please, acceptthis as a gift.\x03Here.\x03I won't allow you to refuse.\x03	L'Arachel...\x03Thank you. I will treasure it.\x03I so wish I had something to giveyou in return...\x03You needn't feel that way.Here, I've an idea...\x03Once we've put an end to all themonstrosities in our lands...\x03Invite me to Renais. Does thisplan please you?\x03	Yes...certainly. Of course.\x03Then we are agreed!\x03Now, you had better notgo dying in battle on me.\x03Not until then, at any rate.Do I have your word?\x03	Yes...let us both live longenough to look back on this time.\x03I am sure that, when we do look back,it will be as the best of friends.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C5C[] = "	,Ah, Eirika.\x03Shall we ride together a while?\x03	Tana, you seem well.\x03And yes, I'd appreciatethe company.\x03I feel I should apologize.\x03I'm afraid I haven't been verymuch help to you, Eirika.\x03To be honest, I'm still in training,and not quite battle-ready.\x03Perhaps you'd fare better if I werenot traveling with you...\x03	Tana, that's not true at all.You've been a great help to us.\x03I have seen you in action. I knowwhat I'm talking about.\x03Thank you, Eirika.\x03Heh... I feel so foolish now.\x03	Why is that?\x03I look on you as a sister, Eirika.\x03And yet, even though we're the sameage, you seem so much more mature.\x03	Hardly...\x03It is you who even gave me thecourage to leave the castle.\x03I wanted to be out on my own, likeyou, to pattern my life after yours.\x03I'm simply glad that we are friends.\x03	Me too, Tana.\x03I'm glad you came. You helpto remind me of better times.\x03";
