const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C61[] = "	Eirika.\x03Forgive the intrusion, but Imust speak to you at once.\x03	Prince Innes?What is it?\x03First, just listen to me.\x03Is there...anyone who laysclaim to your heart?\x03	What?\x03N-no... There'snobody like that.\x03I see. Then let me speak frankly.\x03Eirika, it seems I have fallen inlove with you.\x03	Wh-what!?\x03This is no place for jokes, Innes!Why would you say something like that?\x03This is no joke.I am absolutely serious.\x03These feelings surprise me aswell. I don't know what to do.\x03Fighting at your side all this time,the emotion just exploded within me.\x03I love you. I could not bear tosee you in the arms of another.\x03	P-Prince Innes!\x03I... I...\x03No, Eirika.Do not answer now.\x03I have not yet bested Ephraim. I havenot earned the right to woo you.\x03	Wha--? Why are you bringing mybrother into this?\x03With a man like him around, I can seewhy you show no interest in suitors.\x03If I prove myself his superior, youwill surely accept my hand.\x03If I fail, I release any claim toyour affection.\x03But I swear it on the depth of mylove that I will destroy that man.\x03Eirika, I will expect your answer then.\x03That's all I have to say.\x03	Innes!\x03What an...infuriating man!\x03Why does he have to be so...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C62[] = "Aaaah...\x03		Forde, you're lookingin rare form today.\x03Ah, Princess! Yes, I'm tryingnot to overextend myself today.\x03I see you're looking well, too.\x03Except for...\x03	Yes, Forde?What is it?\x03Well... I was just thinkingabout something...\x03Princess, do you find that your armorleaves a bit too much...exposed?\x03	I beg your pardon?\x03You know, too exposed. Especially aroundthe...er...midriff, if you will.\x03Aren't you worried that, in the heatof battle, it might, eh...\x03	Fly up like this?\x03Augh!Oh... Uh...\x03You were...just joking. Wow.Don't scare me like that!\x03	Oh, I'm sorry. That must haveseemed rather unladylike.\x03Honestly, though, I do ratherlike this armor.\x03It's very easy to move around in.\x03I think that freedom of movement isfar more important to me in combat.\x03Well, sure. I guess everyone hashis own preference.\x03I've gotten many long years of usefrom my armor.\x03	I can imagine.\x03Now that I look at it, I can seeall the scars from all your fights.\x03A knight's greatest pride are the scarshis armor bears for him.\x03This battered shell of mine is the onlytrue badge of valor...\x03...The only real sign that I've weatheredblade and arrow for king and country.\x03	Forde...\x03Oh, and... Well, in my case...\x03Some of these dents are from me fallingoff my horse. Heh...\x03Oh, and some come from falling asleep inmy armor and rolling onto my weapons.\x03Kind of a lot of them, actually.Heh...\x03	You stood by my brother when heand I were separated, didn't you?\x03I never got a chance to thank you.\x03Oh, it was nothing. Really.\x03To be fair, Ephraim probably savedmy hide more often than I his.\x03	I doubt that. My brother rushes intobattle without thought for consequence.\x03I think, if nothing else, you restrainedhis natural recklessness.\x03I owe you a debt. Both you and Kyle.\x03Princess Eirika...\x03	Forde, Renais thanks you. Mayyou always stand beside us.\x03At your service, Princess.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C63[] = "	Princess Eirika! Good to see you.\x03	Ah, Forde. Yes, it's good to haveyou fighting at my side again.\x03It's only because of your skillthat I'm fighting here today.\x03Well, we all seem to be deepin this fight, milady...\x03	Yes, there's no pulling back now.\x03So it would seem. My lady, leavethe fighting to us soldiers.\x03Even if there be an unholy hail of arrows,we would ride into them for your sake.\x03	Ha ha... Why, thank you, sir knight!\x03	...Say, Forde.\x03Yes?\x03	What will you do when allthis fighting is over?\x03When the fighting is over?Hm... Good question.\x03Well...\x03I suppose I'll return to Renais...and take a very, very long nap.\x03	That does sound like you.And then?\x03Then? I would like to returnto my painting, I think.\x03	You paint?\x03Yes, milady. I paint.\x03In the past, I've tried to be quietabout this little hobby of mine.\x03However, quite a few of our grouphave unearthed my hidden secret.\x03	Is that so? Well, I'd love toview your work sometime.\x03Ah, I'd be honored.\x03It's hardly worthy of such an audience,but I'd be glad to show it to you.\x03	I look forward to it.\x03Oh!And...\x03Yes?\x03	Would you ever consider...doing a portrait of me?\x03I'm sorry?\x03	Is that distasteful to you?\x03No! No...\x03It's just that I sorarely do portraits.\x03	So, it would be a bother?\x03Not at all! A bother? Really.\x03This request comes from my princess.I'd be more than happy to.\x03	Thank you, Forde.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C64[] = "	Princess Eirika.\x03	Forde.\x03You asked me earlier what I woulddo when all this fighting ended...\x03	I remember...\x03Well, I should have asked you, too.\x03What will you do when this fighting ends?\x03	Me?\x03Yes.\x03	I......\x03I'd like to restore Renais and bringhappiness back to her people.\x03...Princess Eirika...\x03	It is not enough that this warend...that we go home again.\x03It's not enough that my brotherbecome king.\x03These things aren't enough tomake a good country.\x03...\x03	People deserve happiness. They arethe reason that we rule.\x03Without the people, there can beno Renais.\x03To live happily, to be proudof our nation...\x03To restore the happinessof her people...\x03	Yes, that is my dream now.\x03It is an abstract goal, and perhaps a little vague, but...\x03No, not at all!\x03	How so?\x03I mean, rebuilding a country, nowTHAT is an abstract goal.\x03But what you've described, thatis a wonderful ambition.\x03I've never been so proud toserve the kingdom of Renais.\x03	Forde...\x03I've come to a decision!I know I've already sworn an oath, but...\x03I want to renew that vow. Please, letme help make your dream come true!\x03I'll do anything I can to help you...aslong as it doesn't require heavy lifting.\x03	Thank you...I'm very grateful to you, Forde.\x03It feels like this war might never end,and our people give in to despair quickly.\x03But thanks to people like you, who smilein the face of sorrow, they can be saved.\x03Oh, no. You make too much of it.I'm nothing special.\x03I simply cannot allow myself to worrywhen there's fighting to be done.\x03You're the special one. You have sucha profound effect on us all.\x03	...Me? How so?\x03It is because of you that we can go on.\x03You and the prince are here, riskingyour lives for the cause.\x03Your guidance, your leadership... Itgives us a reason to live as well.\x03	A reason...to live?\x03Yes... To restore that radiantsmile to your own lovely face.\x03	Oh!\x03I fight to see you smile again, todrive the worry from your face.\x03If I can do that, then I will be morethan happy to paint your portrait.\x03	Forde...\x03We'll do it together. Every day isanother step closer to the end of war.\x03One step closer to making your dreamcome true.\x03	...Agreed!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C65[] = "	 	Master Saleh!\x03...\x03	Master?\x03...\x03	...\x03...\x03...Oh, I'm sorry, Princess Eirika.\x03	It's all right.Were you...praying?\x03Not exactly. It'scalled Valega.\x03	Valega?\x03Yes.\x03	What is it?\x03Is it something to do withCaer Pelyn's cultural history?\x03Yes, in a sense. Think of it asa kind of wish. A very pure wish.\x03It is a wish that expands farbeyond individual desire.\x03	I see. I don't claim to understand, butit sounds very interesting.\x03If you don't mind, I'd like tohear more about it later.\x03If you like.\x03	Yes, I would.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C66[] = "	 	Master Saleh.\x03Princess.\x03	What you were telling me aboutValega was most enlightening.\x03It sounds as though you align yourdesires with the world around you.\x03By knowing the vastness of creationaround you, you come to know yourself.\x03And then, by transcending your selfishneeds, you wish for a better world.\x03What you told me, it helped me rediscoverthe importance of that unselfish wish.\x03It's the reason for the war we fightnow... The dream of a better world.\x03Because of your Valega, my ownconviction was renewed.\x03Ahhh. I'm glad to hear that....\x03Princess Eirika, you remind me ofthe warrior princess, Nada Kuya.\x03	Nada Kuya?\x03She's one of Caer Pelyn'sancient heroes.\x03	I'd like to hear about her.\x03I've been told she was a strongwoman, beautiful and proud.\x03She spoke with the voice of nature,and she lived at one with the earth.\x03	But you called her a battle princess...?\x03Well, in ancient times, Caer Pelynwas invaded by a foreign nation.\x03	Really?\x03And leading the charge against theinvaders was Nada Kuya.\x03She carried a narrow sword made from afang gifted to her by the dragonkin.\x03With her dragon blade in her hand,she drove Caer Pelyn's enemies away.\x03	Wow... Quite a story.And you think I--\x03Yes. You remind me of her.\x03	No, no...\x03When Grado invaded Renais, I wasparalyzed. I couldn't do anything.\x03It is only because of the sacrificesof others that I could even escape.\x03But now, you are here. Withyour strength, courage, and dignity.\x03	Master Saleh...\x03If you achieve victory, thelegend will become reality.\x03You will become the Nada Kuyaof this age.\x03	I see... Yes, I see!\x03I have a reason to fight.I have things to protect.\x03I fight for the future. The futureof Renais, the future of my people.\x03Thank you, Master Saleh.\x03Your stories always give me thecourage to fight on.\x03I'm glad to hear that.\x03	I pray your wisdom guidesus through this war.\x03I will do what I can.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C67[] = "	 	...\x03...What troubles you, Princess Eirika?\x03	Oh, Master Saleh.\x03No, nothing. My mind wassomewhere else...\x03Oh, and in the middle ofa battle... I'm sorry.\x03Don't be sorry.\x03I am not going to judge youfor how you think or act.\x03	Thank you.\x03...I was just remembering my home.\x03I was thinking about the lasttime Renais was at peace.\x03...\x03	There were the most beautifulmountains, the clearest rivers...\x03The scent of wildflowers filled theair. The sky was clear and bright.\x03This was before war scarred thehills and scorched the skies.\x03It was a wonderful place. Every daywas filled with hope and possibility.\x03My brother and I would go huntingwith Prince Lyon.\x03...I would make lunches for us. Ephraimwould tease, but Lyon was happy.\x03I... I miss that time so very much.\x03Princess Eirika...\x03I give you my word that you will onceagain see the Renais you love restored.\x03	Master Saleh...I do hope so.\x03But first, you and I must concentrateon the battle at hand. We must win.\x03Thank you, Master Saleh.\x03Your homeland, Caer Pelyn, was alsoa most beautiful place.\x03We had nothing special. But, because ofthat, we had...everything.\x03	I didn't understand that before.\x03Now, I think I know what you mean.\x03I am glad.\x03	When we have to fight no more, please,let me visit you in Caer Pelyn.\x03I would like to know more about yourhome. About Valega and Nada Kuya.\x03You are welcome anytime. Caer Pelynand I will welcome you with open arms.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C68[] = "	Prince Ephraim!\x03	Kyle, what's the matter?\x03Prince Ephraim...\x03You charged at the enemy lineafter you were injured, didn't you?\x03	Oh, that? That was nothing.Don't worry about it.\x03It's not the injury I'm worried about. You'renot supposed to do things like that!\x03	If I retreat at the first scratch,command will fall apart.\x03My lord, you are the future ofRenais, the commander of this army.\x03If something were to happen to you,morale would be shattered.\x03We would lose this war. All becauseof your misplaced pride.\x03	Fine, Kyle. I'll hang back andlet you knights lead the charge.\x03But I don't have time to talkabout this now. I'm leaving.\x03	He says he's going to stop beingso reckless, but I know better.\x03I have to stop him beforehe gets himself killed...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C69[] = "	Do you remember what we agreed tolast time we talked, Prince Ephraim?\x03	Sigh. High command must remain behindthe vanguard and let the soldiers fight.\x03And if he tries to take the van, anyunit, regardless of rank, may stop him.\x03Yes, exactly. So youdo remember it.\x03	And now, every time I try to leadthe charge, my own men stop me!\x03They waste themselves worrying aboutmy safety when their own is at risk.\x03Look, I agreed to your plan at thetime, but this is just ridiculous.\x03I'm going to revoke the order.\x03No, Prince! I know I've told youthis before...\x03But you have to remember, you'rethe future of Renais--\x03	And if we fail because I do notjoin the battle, we have no future!\x03I do know I bear much responsibility,but I simply must revoke the command.\x03I'm sorry, Prince Ephraim, but Ican't allow you to do that.\x03I'm going back to the fight. Makesure you hang back, sire. Go on.\x03	...Sigh... That blasted Kyle.\x03I know that he's simply concernedabout me.\x03Come to think of it, he's alwaysbeen like that.\x03I can't recall a moment when he HASN'Tbeen overly worried about me.\x03But that order really needs to go.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C6A[] = "	My lord prince...I must apologize.\x03	Why is that, Kyle? What doyou need to apologize for?\x03The other day, I was injured onthe battlefield.\x03You raced to my side without amoment's hesitation.\x03As I lost consciousness, I heardyou say something I won't forget.\x03Treat this man as you would my ownbrother. Help him, regardless of cost.\x03	And why must you apologize for that?\x03I ought to have been the one ridingto your aid, my lord.\x03And that you would consider a lowbornknight like myself a brother...\x03All these years, I've thought of myselfas nothing but a loyal retainer.\x03I failed to understand that ourbond runs deeper.\x03	...Since I was a child, you'vetaught me how to be a warrior.\x03A prince is raised to be detached.Distant. To rule the people from above.\x03I could not afford to feel any realaffection for anyone. Just Seth, Forde...\x03And you, Kyle.You were the only ones.\x03I realize that much separates us,but I still consider you family.\x03Although...you do worry about me too much.And you have to stop snapping at me.\x03Prince Ephraim, when I was injured theother day, I came to a realization.\x03I was wrong. The decision I made youagree to the other day was wrong.\x03You belong on the front lines, likeany of the noble warriors of Renais.\x03It will do the men's morale good tosee you fighting at their side.\x03From now on, fight as you must!\x03I will be beside you, and I willprotect you as you fight at our side.\x03	Thank you, Kyle. I was so caught inmy worry that I couldn't fight well.\x03And I will make a concession toyou as well.\x03I will not be so reckless anymore.I know I have an important position.\x03Are we in agreement, Kyle?\x03We are, my lord.Let's ride on together!\x03	Sounds good. Kyle...Don't fall behind!\x03Yes, sire!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C6B[] = "		Hey, Forde...\x03Yes?Oh! What is it, Prince Ephraim?\x03	...What are you hiding?\x03...What are you talking about? We arein the middle of a battle, you know.\x03Pay less attention to me and moreto our enemies!\x03	No, no, Forde. Give it up.Come on--let me see it.\x03...Fine.\x03	...What is that?Is that a painting?\x03This? No, no... No, it'sa topographic map! Yes.\x03For strategy. We need to plotout our strategy, don't we?\x03During battles, I like to look atthis map and analyze enemy lines...\x03	But...that's clearly alandscape painting.\x03...\x03	Did you paint this?\x03Er... Yes. A long time ago.\x03	This is impressive, Forde. You're goodwith both a sword and a brush!\x03You know, when Eirika and I were young,we'd sneak out for long horse rides.\x03We used to watch the sunset sink behindthe mountains while we talked for hours.\x03Your painting reminds me of those days.\x03...Prince Ephraim...\x03	But...during a battle probably isn'tthe right place to indulge your hobby.\x03What if something happened to you?\x03I'm no fool, Prince Ephraim. I alwaysstay alert on the battlefield.\x03I'll cut down any enemy that crossesmy path. Well, Prince... Good luck!\x03	Heh...You're all talk.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C6C[] = "		So, Forde... Not goofingaround today, are you?\x03Of course not! I never fool aroundin a battle.\x03	...Yes, but only in battle.\x03Next to Franz, you seem likeyou're always half asleep.\x03You surely understand how difficult itis to be compared with one's siblings.\x03Next to you, the princess seems sokind and thoughtful. And caring, too!\x03	I see your point. Yes, it's roughbeing held to your sibling's standards.\x03Isn't it, though? So let's stop allthis and get back to the fighting.\x03	...Although...\x03Hm?What is it, Prince Ephraim?\x03	...Eirika has never been farfrom my side--in good times and bad.\x03Without her...I'm not sure I couldlead my people back from this disaster.\x03...I think I understand what youmean, Prince.\x03When we lost our parents, I was shattered.Franz helped me get back on my feet.\x03If I didn't have his help then, I don'tknow where I'd be today...\x03	We are who we are now because theyhave always stood by us.\x03...Let's end this war quickly, Forde.For them. Especially for them.\x03...Yes.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C6D[] = "		How are you doing, Forde?\x03Me? Oh, I'm fine as long as I'vegot a sword in my hand.\x03	...Oh, by the way, Forde.\x03When you have some time, would youshow me your painting again?\x03You'd like to see it? Whythe sudden interest, Prince?\x03	The scene you painted, it's theRenais we once knew...\x03Those magnificent fields and tranquilfarming villages...\x03When I look at it, I can forget, fora second, that we're on a battlefield.\x03I want to restore the Renais you painted.\x03I want to restore these landscapes thatfill me with joy looking at them.\x03I wanted to see the painting again sothat I could carry it with me in my heart.\x03If you like it, Prince Ephraim, I'dbe honored if you would take it.\x03	...Really? Are you sure, Forde?\x03Yes, of course. Please take it.\x03	Thank you, Forde! It is truly beautiful....Did you study painting?\x03No. I just... When we were young,I would paint for Franz.\x03...Our father spent much time away, andFranz wept every night, missing him.\x03But I was just a child, too. I didn'tknow how to make him stop crying.\x03One day, I showed him a drawing thatI'd made of our parents...\x03And Franz stopped crying. I've beenpainting ever since...\x03	...I see...\x03...I've a thought... In exchange for thispainting, there's something you can do.\x03	...What is it, Forde?\x03Once you've achieved your goal, once you'verestored Renais to the way it was...\x03Can I have a vacation?\x03	Is rest all you ever think about? Ifyou want that vacation, earn it!\x03Right, right. I'll just keep riskingmy life protecting you then, Ephraim.\x03	You do that. I'm countingon you, Forde.\x03";
