const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C7C[] = "		You're doing well, Franz.\x03Oh, General!!How are you, sir?\x03I'm so honored that youcame to talk to me.\x03	Must you always overreact?\x03...Honestly, Franz...I'm the one who should feel honored.\x03I beg your pardon?What do you mean, sir?\x03	When I was just a squire, there was oneknight whom I admired above all others.\x03His skill with sword and spear waslegendary. He was truly peerless.\x03We squires learned the meaning ofchivalry watching him serve the king.\x03Ten years back, we received word that aninfamous assassin was hiding in Renais.\x03This knight hunted him down in secrecyso as not to alert the assassin.\x03He hounded the villain and killedhim, but he was mortally wounded...\x03Ten years ago? But that's when--!?\x03No, it couldn't be...\x03	...Yes, Franz.\x03It was the greatest knight in thehistory of Renais. Your father.\x03...I was so young when my father died.\x03And our mother passed away before he did.Forde and I were almost always alone.\x03Oh, I remember how I used to cry like ababe about my father being gone so much.\x03Forde would always remind me, He is servingthe royal family to protect Renais.\x03Forde was so proud of our father, but hewas also a little bit sad.\x03I remember a deep scar he had on hisshoulder, probably in battle.\x03My brother and I used to climb up hisshoulders and vie for his attention.\x03I grew up hearing what a great knight hewas, but I remember only his shoulder.\x03	...You probably have no idea howmuch you resemble your father.\x03Your swordplay, how you tilt the lance,your loyalty to Renais...\x03You've certainly inherited yourfather's spirit.\x03It is an honor to see the skill I onceidolized developing in you, his son.\x03I...I am so flattered to hear that.Thank you very much, General.\x03Someday, I will become a knight evengreater than my brother or my father.\x03To restore Renais, the kingdom to whichI've sworn my blade, I will fight on!\x03	Thank you, Franz. Let's do the best wecan. For Renais, and for your father.\x03Yes, General!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C7D[] = "	Sir Garcia.\x03Your fighting form remains impeccable,despite your years of retirement.\x03Fantastic... How I admire you.\x03	No, General Seth, I still have a longway to go. I've lost so much time.\x03Sir Garcia...\x03	No, no honorifics. I gave up my titleyears ago so I could raise my son.\x03I'm old and rusty, General. The man I amnow is not fit for such fine company.\x03...\x03	But listen, General.\x03I'm not finished yet!\x03What do you mean?\x03	I'm telling you...\x03I'm not yet done!This is not the end of me!\x03	...He has a warrior's heart.\x03Is it pride that keeps him fromaccepting his limitations?\x03I'm afraid that we have awakened an incredible warrior.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C7E[] = "	General.\x03	Garcia.\x03Did you come all this way to talkto me? I'm grateful. Thank you.\x03Don't make a fuss. Might give me secondthoughts before I do it again.\x03	Ah, right. Sorry, sir!\x03Heh...\x03You know, you remind me ofmyself as a young man.\x03	Back when you were in Renais?\x03That's right. Oh, I was so ambitious then,focused on proving myself in battle.\x03His Majesty commended my valor manytimes, he did.\x03	His Majesty always watched over us.\x03Hardworking soldiers received words ofpraise to drive them to greater glories.\x03The lazy ones, he spurred to action,giving them a reason to improve...\x03He was a great king. He earned the trustand respect of his people.\x03...What a loss we've all suffered.\x03	When Castle Renais fell, it was all Icould do to save Princess Eirika.\x03I've never felt so powerless inall my time as a knight...\x03...I was mortified.\x03...I'm sorry. I wasn't blamingyou for King Fado's death.\x03I am the one who surrendered his dutyto live a carefree life with his son.\x03I have no right to cast blame onanyone but myself...\x03	Garcia, you needn't feel that way.\x03You're fighting for Renais again, at theside of her crown prince and princess!\x03There's no shame in that.\x03General Seth...\x03	If you are still true to our late king,then let's win this war together.\x03And together, we shall visit HisMajesty's tomb to report our victory!\x03Yes! You have my word!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C7F[] = "	Garcia.\x03	Ah, General Seth!\x03You seem much recovered from yourpoor spirits the other day.\x03In fact, you seem quite energetic!\x03	I've finally accepted that I'm onlyever truly alive when I'm fighting!\x03Ah, now that is the great GarciaI remember from my youth!\x03Yes, all hesitation is gone fromyour face. You're in rare form!\x03	Yes, and that hesitation is gonefor good, I dare say. Except...\x03Yes?\x03	To tell you the truth...I am notashamed of the life I've lived.\x03I'm not sorry that I abandoned myold life to raise my son.\x03Sir Garcia...\x03	That decision made me who I am now.\x03It's time I embraced both of theseaspects of my past.\x03...\x03	I can only say this in hindsight, but...\x03It is not so bad to have a family.\x03Garcia, I can see it in your eyes.You don't need to tell me.\x03	Heh... I see! Well then, Seth.There is only one solution for it!\x03You should marry! It will do you goodto have a family to go home to.\x03Ah, Garcia...\x03You may be right, but I'm afraid it willtake me some time to get there...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C80[] = "		Oh, General Seth, how do you do?\x03...Sister Natasha, good day to you.\x03I appreciate the care you give our wounded,but be sure to care for yourself, too.\x03I heard about what happened the otherday. It could have turned out badly...\x03	I'm sorry to have worried you. WhenI see an injured person, I must help.\x03I seldom think of the consequencesto myself.\x03I shall be more careful in the future.\x03Grado doesn't know what they've lost,Natasha. You're indispensable to us.\x03If you were injured, our entire strategycould be slowed or lost altogether.\x03Take care of yourself first, andworry about us later.\x03	Seth, you are the one who isindispensable, far more than I am.\x03You race into danger, acting as adecoy or rescuing people alone.\x03You're the one who is reckless.I wish you would watch yourself.\x03I'm sorry. I didn't realize I'dbeen causing you so much worry.\x03I promise to be less reckless. Butyou, don't do anything I wouldn't do.\x03	Yes, General. May you beguided to safety.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C81[] = "	Sister Natasha? Are you well? I heardyou collapsed last night.\x03Maybe you should rest more, insteadof risking yourself on--\x03	Oh, General Seth...I'm sorry about that...\x03We had many wounded, and I drainedmyself healing them all.\x03However, I rested well last night,and I am fully recovered.\x03I'm sorry for giving you so muchcause to worry once again.\x03Oh, boy... You and Eirika...What am I going to do about you?\x03You seem hell-bent on throwingaway your lives in this conflict.\x03	...Oh, I see... I always becomea liability in battle.\x03All I do is cause you worry andconcern.\x03You're always the first to race intobattle to heal an injured person.\x03Do you know what the others havestarted calling you?\x03	...They're calling me names?\x03They've taken to calling you thehealing spirit.\x03	...A healing spirit? Oh, no...I'm far from it. Why, I--\x03...When you first joined us, I wasnot sure I could trust my life to you.\x03You're from Grado, and we've seen thetreacheries of which they are capable.\x03But I've watched you, and I know nowthat I was wrong.\x03I'm grateful for the kindness andcompassion that you've showed us all.\x03My men are right. You are a healingspirit, sent to rejuvenate us all.\x03We're fortunate to have you as ourfriend.\x03	...Friend...?\x03More than a friend. You are anirreplaceable asset to our cause.\x03	Oh, my...I'm sorry...\x03...Please, return to the battle.And may you be guided to safety.\x03...Sister Natasha...\x03If I am injured, I will not be reckless.I will race to your side.\x03And I know that you will take careof me when that happens.\x03	Y-yes, of course I will!Oh, but...I hope that it doesn't.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C82[] = "		General Seth.\x03Sister Natasha. How are you?\x03	Well, thank you. And you?\x03Yes, I'm fine.\x03But it's only because you'vebeen beside me as I've fought.\x03You were always the one toheal my broken body.\x03	You have that wrong, General. You'rethe one constantly rescuing me.\x03When I'm surrounded by enemies, whenI'm separated from the others...\x03Sister Natasha... Do you plan onreturning to Grado someday?\x03	...Yes. I must return to the temple.Our people need my services.\x03Is that...what you really want?\x03	...General Seth...\x03Could anything sway you tostay in Renais instead?\x03	...General Seth, what are you...\x03...I'm sorry. I'm--\x03I'll be more direct.Sister Natasha...\x03When this war is over wouldyou...come live with me?\x03	Oh!\x03But, Seth... I'm a cleric.I'm sworn never to...\x03I know you're a cleric. You've givenyour life over to a divine calling.\x03But would the Everlasting not smileupon the love shared by its creations?\x03	...Seth, I--Yes, I believe so.\x03I vow upon the sacred oaths you havesworn that I will make you happy.\x03	Seth... I hope youkeep that promise.\x03I'll wait for you until thiswar is finally at an end.\x03I will keep my promise, Natasha.\x03I will.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C83[] = "	You're pretty good with a spear.\x03	Thank you.\x03I don't think I've introduced myself.I'm the leader of the Knights of Renais--\x03I know you. Of course I know you.You're General Seth, the Silver Knight.\x03	...Yes, that's right.\x03And you are Cormag, the renownedwyvern rider of Grado.\x03If the legendary Silver Knight knowsmy name, I can't be doing too bad, huh?\x03	You and your brother, Glen, are famouseven among the Knights of Renais.\x03We have no wyvern riders in Renais, andyour stories are favorites among the men.\x03I've been watching your combat stylesince you joined our forces.\x03Oh, is that so? Well, tellme: what do you think?\x03	I'd love a chance to spar with you.\x03Not a chance. I couldnever beat you.\x03	So you say, but I can see in your eyesthat you'll never accept failure.\x03Heh...\x03And all this time, I thought youwere just another loyal dullard.\x03Guess I was wrong. We shouldchat some more sometime.\x03	Yes, I think I'd like that.\x03Perhaps once things have eased up.I'm looking forward to it, Cormag.\x03Sure thing.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C84[] = "		Hey, Seth.\x03Ah, Cormag. Good timing.\x03I had something I wanted to ask you.Your family, are they all soldiers?\x03	Why do you ask?\x03Your skill with the spear is amazing.Have you trained since you were a child?\x03	No, I come from a long line of dirt-poorfarmers. I wielded a plough, not a spear.\x03When we were kids, Glen and I had tochase birds and animals from our fields.\x03We used sticks and stones, and I thinkthat helped with our aim, to be honest.\x03Is that so...So why did you join the army?\x03	It's a funny story, really.\x03...The emperor's caravan passed throughour village one day.\x03My brother and I watched the gloriousprocession from the top of a tree.\x03Then, a stray dog started to harry thehorses pulling the emperor's carriage.\x03We threw rocks to drive off the mutt,but some soldiers decided to arrest us.\x03Why? You were trying to help...\x03	Yes, well. We didn't just hit the dog.We got a few of the soldiers as well.\x03Ah-ha...So, what happened next?\x03	Well, the emperor shows up in the roomthe soldiers had thrown us.\x03He looks around and, in this very calmbut stern voice, says to the soldiers:\x03\"What are you men doing, arresting merechildren? They were trying to help!\"\x03Then, he invites us to dine at his table,and it was a luxurious feast, I tell you!\x03Now, we were just kids. We lacked thebasic courtesies. We were just filthy.\x03And we kept droning on about the mostidiotic things: chores, the village...\x03But he listened to us intently, andthat fatherly smile never left his face.\x03And he said, You lads are good atdriving off dogs with stones...\x03Your skills are wasted in the fields. Let'ssee how you fare with spears instead.\x03And that's how you were recruited.\x03	Exactly. It's difficult to ignoresuch a commanding presence.\x03But...the emperor changed. I stillcan't believe what's happened.\x03...I was born into a family of knights, soit was a given that I should be one, too.\x03I trained in spear and sword. I studiedchivalry and swore my oaths of fealty.\x03And because of my hard work, the lateKing Fado treated me like a second son.\x03...It's funny. You and I are from differentworlds, but we share the same loyalties.\x03	True...\x03But King Fado is dead now.\x03And my emperor is the onewho killed him...\x03My emperor is as goodas dead to me.\x03...I already serve a new lord.\x03Cormag, you will find a rulerworthy of your loyalties, too.\x03	Yeah, I hope so...\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C85[] = "		Can I have a word with you, Cormag?\x03Oh, Seth. Of course.What can I do for you?\x03	I've been thinking about your story,and I've come to a decision.\x03Hm? What are you talking about?\x03	...Cormag, listen.\x03As general of the Knights of Renais,I'd like to offer you a post.\x03What? You want me to jointhe Knights of Renais?\x03	Yes, exactly.\x03I've been watching you fight, and I'vebeen thinking about this for some time.\x03Since we've been speaking, I've seenmore than just your fighting prowess.\x03I've seen that you're a strong andnoble person as well.\x03You are a man I would risk my lifefighting beside.\x03Prince Ephraim will be a great king.Would you fight for him with me?\x03I really appreciate it.Thanks, Seth.\x03But...Grado is my home. I can't tradeloyalties to Renais just like that.\x03	...I knew you would say that.\x03Emperor Vigarde is my only lord.\x03My duty now is to correct themistakes he has made.\x03That's why I'm here. I hopeyou can understand.\x03	Yes, of course...Still, I'm glad that I met you.\x03Same here, Seth. Now, let's getthis war over with, shall we?\x03	Yes, and when it's done, we'll gettogether and tell some stories.\x03I'm looking forward to it!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C86[] = "	Say, Sir Gilliam, canI ask you a question?\x03	What is it, Franz?\x03Are you disturbed about fighting with me?\x03	Why would you say something like that?\x03You and I are from different lands.We have different backgrounds...\x03I thought that might've madeyou feel uncomfortable.\x03	Blast. I don't need to answer that.\x03\x13Sir Gilliam!\x03	Listen: I'm here by my king's order, andby his order alone.\x03I'm well aware that we have diversebackgrounds and experiences.\x03I don't care who I pair up with. You can'talways have your own way.\x03That's just how it works in Frelia. It'sluck of the draw, you follow?\x03Do they let you swap partners until youfind that special someone back in Renais?\x03Oh, no! No, no, no... That'snot what I meant.\x03It's just... I was worried that I might beslowing you down with my lesser skills.\x03	Franz, you're wasting your time worryingwhen there are better things to be done.\x03Like what?\x03	Like training, of course.\x03Quit your worrying and show me howgood a Knight of Renais can be.\x03I could ask for nothingbetter. Please!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C87[] = "	Franz, I can see yourtraining has paid off.\x03	Yes, and I have to say, I'm surprised.I feel the energy flowing through me.\x03I think it's because of my resistancetraining, actually.\x03Frelia's resistance training, you mean.\x03You mean to tell me that you haveno training like that in Renais?\x03	We do have a system to strengthen our chest, arms, shoulders, and legs.\x03However, that's where we stop. We don'ttrain each individual finger...\x03Every muscle acts in relation to each othermuscle. How can you neglect the fingers?\x03That's how we Frelians think.\x03	Fascinating how our countries can havesuch distinct training systems, isn't it?\x03And you've been training with our systemevery day without a single complaint!\x03I'm impressed.\x03	Oh, that's because, each night beforeI go to sleep...\x03I do our traditional relaxation exercises.\x03Relaxation exercises?\x03	Before going to bed, flex each muscle youused, and you'll wake up feeling refreshed.\x03What, no fatigue the following day?\x03	That's right. That's what it's for.\x03That's wonderful!\x03	I can teach you if you like.\x03Please.\x03	Fantastic! We'll start tonight!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C88[] = "		Well, Franz, it looks like there'sa lot I can learn from Renais.\x03Why the change of heart, Sir Gilliam?\x03	I've been doing your exercises everynight, and I feel fantastic.\x03I'm glad you like it.\x03	I appreciate Renais muchmore, thanks to you.\x03Really?I'm glad.\x03I'm thrilled that the great Sir Gilliamapproves of the training in Renais.\x03	Thrilled? You're overreacting.\x03No, honestly! I am thrilled. It'sa small thing, I know...\x03But when someone recognizes the finequalities of Renais, I get a thrill.\x03Renais is a small country, but itcontains much that is good.\x03	I don't know Renais, but I do knowhow you feel as a fellow knight.\x03The more we are away, the more wethink back on our beloved homeland.\x03I'm glad that I'm not alone in this.\x03	Chin up, lad. Be proud of your country,Franz, Knight of Renais.\x03As your friend from neighboring Frelia,I'm glad you're proud of your home.\x03Yes, Sir Gilliam!Thank you very much!\x03";
