const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C9A[] = "	How are your ears today, Moulder?Can you still hear that melody?\x03	No, I haven't heard it for a while.I guess it was a hallucination after all.\x03Regardless of the cause, I'm gladthat you don't hear it anymore.\x03	I'm relieved, too, but...I alsomiss it somewhat.\x03The melody was haunting me, andI finally remember what it was.\x03And? What was the song?\x03	That was the music played at King Hayden's coronation. \x03Frelia's coronation hymn.\x03Ah, I remember it well...\x03It is a strong song, and Frelia'sknightly choir performed it well.\x03	I was the one who carriedthe crown to the throne.\x03I was so nervous that Imight drop it!\x03I remember that you were the oneto bear that regal burden.\x03I was a mere recruit, stuck inthe back with the other whelps.\x03You know, I remember now... Yourhands shook like you were frozen!\x03	Yes, and then someone shouted, in a loudvoice, Get ahold of yourself, man!\x03The crown slipped, and I fumbled tocatch it! I was so embarrassed.\x03I'm so sorry.I was young.\x03You know, I felt so bad that I havespent years making it up to you.\x03I acted before I thought. I'm sorryfor all the embarrassment I caused.\x03	That's right! I believe I metyou the very next day.\x03Aha! I've figured it out!\x03Figured what out?\x03	That melody--I could only hear itwhen I was with you. That means...\x03Yes?\x03	It was a sign. A sign from above thatwe must both return to the basics.\x03Return to the basics? What does--Ah. Of course.\x03	Yes. We must remember who we were andwhat drove us to join this cause.\x03I believe you are right...\x03";
