const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C9E[] = "		Vanessa, how are you holding up?\x03Father Moulder.\x03We are struggling, butI'll pull through somehow.\x03Say, Father Moulder...\x03	You want to know about PrinceInnes, don't you? He's doing well.\x03I was worried for a moment,but he'll be fine.\x03Oh!\x03I, uh... Thank you....\x03How did you know?\x03	Well...\x03You see, as a priest, I've metpeople from all walks of life.\x03Some of them--like you--well, Ican read them like an open book.\x03You...can read my mind?That's so...embarrassing.\x03	No, no. It's not like that. I just meanyou are a pure, straightforward girl.\x03That's a compliment worthy of a knight.\x03Do you think so?Thank you, Father.\x03	Hm. Say, would you like to heara story from the prince's youth?\x03I'd like that, Father. Very much!\x03	Hm...Oh my!\x03You know, I think we'd bettertake care of our enemies, first.\x03Look out!Over there!\x03Stay here, Father. I'lltake care of this.\x03	Yes, I think that would be best.\x03Tell me your story another time,though. I'd like to hear it.\x03	I'd be delighted.Another time, then.\x03Yes, Father!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0C9F[] = "		Well, do you have timefor that story I promised?\x03Certainly, Father.\x03	It was over ten years ago, whenthe prince was just a child.\x03There was a ceremony at the castle,with a trick archer of sorts.\x03A trick archer?\x03	Yes. He was a very famous and undeniablyskilled archer from abroad.\x03He was to shoot a tiny target that hadbeen placed in the distance.\x03However, in the middle of the show,someone stopped him from shooting.\x03Oh, no... It wasn't--\x03	Yes, it was young Prince Innes.\x03He said, That's not far enough!Move the target back farther!\x03Then, he insisted on trying himself.\x03That's so like him!\x03	Isn't it?King Hayden tried to stop him, but...\x03Well, you know how he is.He doesn't listen to anyone.\x03And so, it became a contest between ourprince and this foreign archer.\x03So, what happened?\x03	First, they established the ground rules.\x03Each person was to shoot at the target. Ifboth arrows hit, they increased the range.\x03They simply continued to move the targetback until one person missed the mark.\x03Sounds simple enough.\x03	Ah, but the two were evenly matched.Every shot was a perfect bull's-eye.\x03The crowd cheered, and the targetmoved ever farther back...\x03But then it came to the turning point.The foreign archer said, \x03This is no test. Let's move thetarget back more.\x03It seemed like bravado, but the archeractually had a clever tactic in mind.\x03Clever? How so?\x03	They had been shooting for some time,and the archer's arms had grown weary.\x03Precision archery is far more taxingthan the battlefield, you see.\x03So even though he was a skilled archer,he was at the limits of his endurance.\x03He was still hitting the mark accurately,but his arm was quivering more and more.\x03Everyone knew that the prince wason the verge of victory.\x03I don't understand. They were shooting atthe same target, shot for shot, right?\x03Why would moving the target make anydifference?\x03	Yes, they were still shooting at thesame target.\x03However, the archer suggested that theymove the target much farther away...\x03Much farther than any child Innes's agecould hope to loose an arrow to.\x03Oh, that IS clever!\x03	Even the archer, with his trained arms,was firing at his maximum range.\x03In fact, he almost missed the target!\x03Then, it was the prince's turn.\x03And...?\x03	It was clearly too far away for theyoung prince to hit the target.\x03But His Highness was undeterred. He drewhis string and fired up into the sky.\x03The arrow did not merely hit the target.No, it was a perfect bull's-eye!\x03You see, the prince arced his shotto extend his range beyond its limits.\x03To hit a target this way requiresincredible skill, but the prince did it.\x03And then he turned to the archer and said,Shall we move the target back farther?\x03The archer looked so crestfallen. Headmitted defeat, and it was settled.\x03That's amazing...\x03	That it is.\x03Thank you very much, FatherMoulder! That's incredible!\x03I'm even more--\x03	More...what?\x03Oh...No, nothing.\x03	I'm glad you liked the story.\x03Keep up the good work, Vanessa.\x03Yes, sir!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0CA0[] = "		I'm glad to see you well, Vanessa. Youdo your fellow pegasus knights proud.\x03We are blessed to have you fightingat our side.\x03You credit us warriors too much, Father.Without healers, we would all be lost.\x03Nothing I say can tell you how muchI value your presence here.\x03	We are all doing ourpart in this war.\x03No need to thank me.\x03I'm serious!\x03Without your help, we wouldnever survive these skirmishes!\x03	I'm gratified by that.Thank you.\x03Father... Thank you againfor the other day.\x03	Hmm?Oh, you mean that story?\x03Yes.\x03	Ah...\x03You know, you remind me ofmyself, twenty years back.\x03Huh?\x03	Oh, never mind......\x03Good luck to you, Vanessa.\x03I don't know where this will lead, butI'm sure the prince knows your feelings.\x03Father Moulder, I only aspire to beworthy of his greatness.\x03I expect nothing in return.\x03	Are you sure?\x03...\x03	Well, do what you think is best for you.\x03We all carry many burdens... To country,family, duty, honor...\x03However, we are all ultimately freeto embrace or reject those burdens.\x03If you find yourself in need ofspiritual guidance, speak to me.\x03Father Moulder, you're so kind.\x03Thank you. I'm so grateful tohave you on the field with me.\x03	Vanessa, we fight for the greater good.\x03We fight for our country, for ourfriends, and...for ourselves.\x03You're right, Father.In so many things.\x03";
