const char gCompressedText_MSG_0CA9[] = "	+	Hi, Syrene.Thanks for talking the other day.\x03Are you feeling better now?\x03	Well... It's not that easy, butI quit comparing myself with you.\x03You might not know this, but there'ssomething about you I've always envied.\x03	About me?What do you mean?\x03You have an inner fortitude that I will never be able to match.\x03	Inner...fortitude?\x03Do you remember when Father collapsed?\x03Mother and I were so panicked that we didn't know what to do.\x03You were the youngest of us all,\x03but you gathered nuts in your small handsand went to the village to sell them.\x03Then you came home with medicine for him.\x03	Well, I don't know what to say.\x03When you face a difficult circumstance,your true self emerges.\x03You were very young, but had the presenceof mind and ingenuity to help Father.\x03You comforted me and Mother, and yourescued Father.\x03I've always respected your strength,and wished for some of it myself.\x03	But...you were the one who joined the Knights at such an early age,\x03and it was you who supported our family.\x03I emulated your strength. I wanted to support my family like you did.\x03It's always been my goal. And I respect you more than anyone else.\x03I wish you could be as confident in yourselfas I am of you.\x03No matter what, you'll always be all right.\x03	All right, then. I have to tell you!The person I love is--\x03Wait, Vanessa!Wait until the war is over to tell me.\x03When everything is over, bring him home.\x03I'll go home a little ahead of you, and wait for you two with Father and Mother.\x03We'll make your favorite meal... Is that enough to convince you?\x03	Yes.\x03I'll do my best... For this war and also for him.\x03That's my girl. Don't worry.You'll be all right.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0CAA[] = "	Pegasus!\x03	You must be Lute!\x03And who are you?\x03	I'm Vanessa.I'm captain of Frelia's pegasus knights.\x03And this here is Titania. We're both pleased to meet you, Lute.\x03Ah, the pegasus, the proud, winged horse.\x03You know, they only attach to someone theyaccept as their master.\x03And did you know that pegasi fly by kickingthe air, not by flapping their wings.\x03It's a common misconception, but wingsare mainly used for gliding.\x03	...Yes, as captain, I learned allthis long ago. \x03Plus, if they flapped their wings constantly,no one would be able to ride them.\x03In some countries, the word pegasus means fountain or ocean.\x03Different cultures have different storiesabout the creation of the pegasus.\x03In one legend, there was a monster whocould turn anyone into stone.\x03When the monster died, its blood seeped intothe ground. There, a pegasus was born. \x03	Interesting... You are very knowledgeable.\x03I know.\x03	...Well! Thank you for the lesson. I'm glad we're on the same team.\x03It was nice meeting you.\x03Yes, nice to meet you, Titania.\x03		I'm Vanessa!\x03";
