const char gCompressedText_MSG_0CF4[] = "		...Hello, Cormag.\x03What's the matter? You've gotyour gloomy face on again.\x03	Doesn't this all get hard for you?\x03This what?\x03	...\x03Ever since this started, we've beenfighting nothing but Grado soldiers.\x03These are our countrymen.Our families...\x03......\x03	Every battle we win, I see only howmany casualties we've caused.\x03I'm a healer, but to win this, Imust turn my back on my countrymen.\x03I have to let them suffer, whenall I want to do is help them.\x03But...\x03...But what?\x03	Grado is responsible for all ofthis. Our homeland...\x03Grado has caused so many deaths now.We have no choice but to fight.\x03Ah. You see it now. That's thesad irony of the battlefield.\x03I ride a wyvern and use my spear tobring low men who should be my allies.\x03We each joined this cause in hopes ofbringing Grado to its senses.\x03Our country has set the world on itsear, and it's up to us to right things.\x03	I suppose...\x03...You know something, Natasha?\x03You should never be ashamed ofthe fact that you're from Grado.\x03You have no debt to pay, no burdenof guilt to bear.\x03Grado was once a magnificent country.Do what you can to restore that glory.\x03It took only a handful of men to turnGrado down the wrong path,\x03but perhaps a mere handful of soldierscan set things right again.\x03	I understand, Cormag. I'll do whatI know to be right, no matter what.\x03I feel like a heavy fog has beenlifted from my heart. Thank you.\x03Ah, I just wanted to see that lovelysmile on your face again.\x03You and me, we've got lots to talkabout, I think. Let's do this again.\x03	I'd love to.\x03";
