const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D21[] = "	 Gerik...\x03	Hm? What is it, Saleh?You look even more serious than usual.\x03Gerik...You truly despise me, don't you?\x03	Huh?!What?\x03I...\x03	...\x03Your friend, I...\x03	Don't say it, Saleh!That was an act of fate. Right?\x03All you did was brush those sparksaway from yourself.\x03Gerik...\x03	Listen, we're mercenaries.\x03We end up working together with old foes,and crossing blades with former allies.\x03It's just part of the job.\x03My friend Zabba died by your act.That much is true.\x03And at that moment, I could think of nothing but avenging him!\x03But after that, you saved my life...\x03We became friends.That's the truth of it, isn't it?\x03Yes...\x03	I trust you now.You are my friend.\x03I'm not lying to you.I don't lie to my friends.\x03That's something I don't do.\x03And you are my friend.\x03Since that day, it's you whohas saved me time and time again.\x03	We're all human after all.Helping our friends is part of our nature.\x03Gerik...\x03You...You're a good man...\x03	That's enough of that! You keep that upand I'll be blushing like a schoolgirl.\x03Ha!\x03	Hey! Ha ha ha! I caught a rareglimpse of you smiling.\x03Listen, Saleh, I know we're risking our liveshere, but this war's not our whole lives.\x03Let's not do anything stupid.We're going to get past this.\x03Then you're going to haul your carcass backto Caer Pelyn and care for the elder!\x03Yes...And you'll visit, too.\x03	Sure. When things calm downI'll let you throw me a feast.\x03I can't wait to have Caer Pelyn'sfamous mutton stew again.\x03We'll be waiting for you, Gerik.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D22[] = "	!Hey, Tethys!Check out my magic!?\x03	Ewan! How many times am I going tohave to say it?\x03This isn't a field trip.Please promise me you'll behave.\x03Oh, you don't have to worry about me.\x03But since I'm here, I'd like to be ofuse. Otherwise I'm just in the way.\x03You gotta let me do something.\x03	You have a point, butyou're still too young.\x03Too young? I'm not a child anymore!I can look after myself!\x03	What are you talking about?You're not a full-fledged mage, are you?\x03Well, no, not yet. But someday I'm gonnabe one of the best mages ever!\x03These soldiers recognize my talent. That'swhy I'm here on the battlefield.\x03Just watch me! You wouldn't say that I'mtoo young or inexperienced if you saw me!\x03	\nWait! Ewan, wait up!\x03Oh, he's gone...\x03Only a child would say something like,Just watch me.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D23[] = "	!	Hey, Tethys. You've been getting prettychummy with that guy lately.\x03What do you mean, Ewan?Who's that guy?\x03	You know, THAT guy.Look, he's right over there...\x03And that guy waving his sword around...\x03I'd say you've been a little too friendlywith all of them!\x03Too friendly? I wonder. I thinkchatting now and again is normal.\x03Wait a minute...Ewan, are you feeling jealous?\x03		D-don't be stupid.That's not it at all!\x03Hold on.\x03You know, that man told me he founda frog in his boots the other day.\x03And that man woke up to findhalf his moustache shaved off.\x03You wouldn't know anything aboutthat, would you?\x03	N-no. This is the first I've heard of it.\x03Really?\x03	Um, yeah...\x03Ooh! It WAS you, wasn't it?\x03Ewan, you can't do things like that.Even if it is kind of funny.\x03	But they're morons! All they do is getyou to dance, and then they run around\x03on the battlefield challenging each otherto contests of strength and valor!\x03They're dumb braggarts, and I was justtaking 'em down a peg.\x03But I'm not jealous!\x03All right, all right.\x03I'll keep your secret this time, but you must stop!\x03	They're the troublemakers, you know?Oh...OK. I got it.\x03I'll leave 'em alone.But, Tethys?\x03What is it?\x03	I'll always be here to protect you.I'm not too young for that!\x03So instead of always helping those guys,dance for me once in a while.\x03I know it'll make me stronger!\x03Ewan...\x03	I'll see you later!You gotta promise to dance for me!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D24[] = "	!It's not such a good idea for youto dance too close to the front lines.\x03	Hee hee!Thanks for worrying about me, Ewan.\x03But are you sure it's not just thejealousy talking?\x03Th-that's not it at all!It's dangerous! That's it!\x03	I'm sorry, I'm sorry.But you know, Ewan...\x03Since you joined up with the army,you really have gotten stronger.\x03I have, haven't I?So I'm no longer a novice, right?\x03	No, you've truly grown.I'm glad, but also a little sad.\x03Hmm. So when I'm a full-fledgedmage, you're gonna be sad?\x03	I guess so. A little sad, anyways.\x03I'm so much older than you that I'vealways thought of you as a child.\x03That's why I always thought I hadto protect you.\x03You know, at the beginning of all of this I really was treating it like a game.\x03Then I saw the dangers you faced tohelp everyone.\x03I knew I couldn't treat it like a gameany longer.\x03\x13Battles threaten people's lives and needto end quickly.\x03That's why I need to boost my powers.I want to help you and the others.\x03I have to become a full-fledged mageto really do my part.\x03So, don't be sad.I just want to protect you...\x03	Ewan...\x03	You've been looking after your littlebrother for so many years.\x03Now it's my turn to return the favor.I mean, I am the man of the family.\x03So from now on, I'm gonna be helping you out.\x03\nThank you, Ewan. Hearing you saythat makes me very happy.\x03It proves to me how much you'vetruly grown.\x03But that doesn't mean you need torush off on your own or anything.\x03If I thought you didn't need meanymore, I would feel really sad.\x03There's no reason to get all weepy.\x03No matter how old I get, you'll alwaysbe my big sister. My one and only.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D25[] = "	Say, Marisa, you're left-handed, right?\x03	How did you know that?\x03Well, when you're carrying a sword, don'tyou always have it in your left hand?\x03	No, I can use either hand...But my left hand is stronger.\x03So that's like a warning sign:left hand equals danger.\x03	Warning sign...\x03So why is it you always sleep on yourright side?\x03You know you never roll overin your sleep?\x03And even the slightest noise causes youto spring up. Do you ever really sleep?\x03	I have to do that.Otherwise I wouldn't survive.\x03Wouldn't survive?You must be exaggerating.\x03	I sleep with my dominant arm up.\x03That way, if I'm attacked, my good armis ready to go.\x03Huh...\x03Do all sword fighters sleep that way?\x03	If your dominant arm is cut, you'reat a disadvantage in battle.\x03That means death.\x03But doesn't your arm ever fall asleep?Aren't there times when you can't use it?\x03	No. My father trained me when I wasa child, so that doesn't happen.\x03When you were a child? How?Kids always roll around in their sleep.\x03	My father placed blunt swords at my sideswhen I slept to keep me from moving.\x03Your father did that?But that's so dangerous...\x03	No, the blades were rounded and dull. And itworked. I don't roll over when sleeping.\x03Wow, sword fighters have some intensetraining methods, don't they?\x03I'm glad I was an average kid. I mean, Iwas poor, but at least I slept freely.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D26[] = "	Tethys.Are you right-handed?\x03	Will wonders never cease?You actually started a conversation.\x03When you dance, you oftenbegin by putting your right foot forward.\x03	Now I'm really amazed.I can't believe you noticed.\x03But footwork in dancing has nothing to dowith being right- or left-handed.\x03Dancing is a way of expressing feelingsthrough body movement.\x03All of one's experiences are incorporatedand displayed in the way one dances.\x03Experiences?What kind of experiences?\x03	That, my dear, is my little secret.Mine may be a bit unique, though.\x03My life's taken some odd turns, but it'sbecause of them that I started dancing.\x03And when I'm dancing, I'm happy.\x03Hmmm.Your dances give people courage.\x03Dancing suits you.\x03	Doesn't it, though?All the mercenaries tell me that, too.\x03Now that you understand my dancing, you'retruly a member of Gerik's team.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D27[] = "	Tell me, Marisa, have you ever thoughtabout wanting to be reborn?\x03	Reborn?\x03You know, coming back as someone elseafter you die?\x03If you were going to be reborn,what would you like to be?\x03Perhaps a beautiful dancer like me?\x03	I'm fine with being me.I can't imagine anything else.\x03I thought that's what you'd say.\x03Actually, I thought of lots of things, butreally can't imagine any other life.\x03I guess that means that in spite of all thehardships we've faced, we're really happy.\x03	I suppose so...\x03Living in this age means that we face many bad things and then worse things. Yet...\x03We're alive, so that means we also getgood things and then better things, too.\x03In tough times, I sometimes think I'd liketo be reborn in another time, but the\x03important thing is to not give up and tolive your life to the fullest.\x03	When you die, life is over.There's no such thing as being reborn.\x03Well, you may be right.\x03	We only get one chance.So all I can do is keep fighting.\x03After all's said and done, you trulylike who and what you are, right?\x03We have completely different lives, butwe have that in common.\x03That and the same man, right?\x03	What?!What do you mean?!?\x03You can't hide it from me.\x03I guess I should ask,do you think you're hiding it?\x03		I-I'm hiding nothing.Nothing at all!\x03What an interesting reaction.Youth is so cute.\x03		Wh-why are you smiling?!Ah...\x03Don't be embarrassed.\x03We're going to be around each other for along time. We should talk.\x03		I've got to go!\x03There's no need to run away.We may be rivals, but we're still friends.\x03		I'm not running away!I'm just...leaving!\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D28[] = "	$Are you Tethys, the dancerwho captivates all audiences?\x03	Who are you?\x03Oh, you don't know me?That's so disappointing.\x03I am Rennac of Carcino.I beg your indulgence...\x03	It's a pleasure to meet you, Rennac.\x03However, I'm a bit busy at the moment.Perhaps we could talk another time.\x03Is that so? Very well then.Another day.\x03	Yes.\x03And perhaps I could have youdance for me and me alone.\x03	Hm?\x03I will of course dance if you ask, but...For you and you alone?\x03Are you perhaps attempting to woo me?If that's the case, you should stop. I've...\x03No, no, that's not what Iwas intending at all.\x03Yet many women who say they're notinterested end up in my arms all the same.\x03	Well, if that's the case,maybe I'll keep my eye on you.\x03If you turn out to be such a catch,I may rethink my stance.\x03It's a deal then.\x03I ask that you observe myconduct closely.\x03Good day.\x03	Oh, dear...I think he took me seriously.\x03I hope he doesn't get hishopes up too high.\x03";
