const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D49[] = "	%)	Don't tell me you've joinedup here as well, have you?\x03...General Duessel.\x03Prince Lyon no longer holds the capital.\x03My reason for remaining is gone...\x03	Knoll, I have somethingI would ask you.\x03What exactly happened toHis Majesty and Prince Lyon?\x03......\x03Do you have the courage tohear that answer?\x03I think perhaps that it will notbe an answer you want to hear.\x03	What does that mean?\x03Are you familiar with a certain foreignanecdote of comedic nature?\x03It involves two starving menand a single loaf of bread.\x03If they break the loaf in two,both men will die of starvation...\x03	Knoll, I'm not asking for a riddle.Let's not waste any more time here.\x03I'm ready to hear the truth. Nothingyou tell me could surprise me.\x03If that is your wish, GeneralDuessel... I will speak frankly.\x03This is something that PrinceLyon does not know.\x03Something that no one should know.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D4A[] = "	%)We students of ancient magic, alongwith Prince Lyon himself,\x03were researching certain arcanetechniques lost long ago.\x03We were able to reproduce one...phenomenon, but only briefly.\x03	......\x03I should be more concise.\x03Prince Lyon and I pierced theveil that clouds our futures.\x03	What? You...could see intothe future?\x03How is that possible? What magicis powerful enough to--\x03Time is like the water of a river:it flows ever on, never stopping.\x03Certain disturbances can cause ripplesthat speed swiftly downstream.\x03If you can see the water, you can readthe flow, the ripples, the waves.\x03	Hmm...\x03It is possible, General. Possibleand, at times, easy. Just think of it:\x03If you knew a storm was coming in advance,you could evacuate everyone in its way.\x03If you could see what was to come, youcould help those who might have died.\x03Prince Lyon explained this to us withmuch joy in his voice and heart.\x03His power would, at long last, be ableto help the citizens of Grado.\x03	......\x03We continued our work. There wereceremonies, rituals--such horrors...\x03And then we saw it.\x03In the near future, Grado would beravaged by catastrophe.\x03	A catastrophe? Do you...\x03No, it's not the conflict in whichwe are currently embroiled.\x03This event is still in our future.\x03We saw Grado. We saw the earthcrumble. We saw our people dying.\x03We saw the shape our future would take.\x03	What?That's madness... Idiocy!\x03I've lived a long life, and I'venever heard of anything like that.\x03Not ever.\x03I am not surprised that you do notbelieve me, General.\x03We could not believe it, either. Wetried to disprove what we had seen.\x03But nothing could shake the vision.\x03In this disaster, Grado would bedestroyed. Countless would die.\x03Those who died quickly would bespared the slow horror of starvation.\x03This was when the emperor died, by theway. Lyon was shattered by despair.\x03He devoted himself to research, andthen came the Dark Stone...\x03	So that's what happened?\x03Is that when the decisionto invade Renais was made?\x03I don't know.\x03Only one person knowsthe truth behind that.\x03	......\x03I have told you only thetruths I have seen.\x03";
const char gCompressedText_MSG_0D4B[] = "	%)......\x03	Knoll.\x03Is that you, General Duessel?\x03	You're tired, aren't you?Worn to the bone.\x03I understand how you feel, but on thebattlefield, this only invites death.\x03You are probably right...\x03And yet that might be best.\x03	What are you planning todo from here on?\x03I do not know...\x03I have lost my way.\x03Perhaps I should have beenexecuted in the capital.\x03	......\x03I once studied dark magicalongside Prince Lyon.\x03He was such a gentle soul. You couldsee it--he was too kind to survive.\x03Prince Lyon dreamt of finding happinessfor all of Grado's citizens.\x03	......\x03And now, Prince Lyon is no more.\x03I have lost everything.\x03	I have also lost everything.\x03And we have both lost our ways.\x03We are dead men who have stayedtoo long away from our graves.\x03But remember, Knoll...\x03You cannot see the future, but youcan look back at your past.\x03Look and learn. And remember.\x03What gave your life meaning, and whathas taken meaning from you now?\x03......\x03	If you still hold the convictions thatguided you in Grado, you can start anew.\x03That... That is what I must do.\x03We may be diminished by our shame, butwe are not dead yet, my friend.\x03General Duessel...\x03I am not as strong as you.\x03Still, I believe you are right.I, too, shall search for a new path.\x03A path that guides me to realizing thedreams Prince Lyon once held so dear.\x03";

